	white on one side."
The computer scientist : "Oh, no!  A special case!"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(562,'fortunes',58,'A bird in the bush usually has a friend in there with him.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(563,'fortunes',59,'A bird in the hand is worth two in the bush.
		-- Cervantes');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(564,'fortunes',47,'A bird in the hand is worth what it will bring.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(565,'fortunes',59,'A bird in the hand makes it awfully hard to blow your nose.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(566,'fortunes',48,'A bit of talcum
Is always walcum
		-- Ogden Nash');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(567,'fortunes',94,'A black cat crossing your path signifies
that the animal is going somewhere.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(568,'fortunes',954,'A book is the work of a mind, doing its work in the way that a mind deems
best.  That''s dangerous.  Is the work of some mere individual mind likely to
serve the aims of collectively accepted compromises, which are known in the
schools as ''standards''?  Any mind that would audaciously put itself forth to
work all alone is surely a bad example for the students, and probably, if
not downright antisocial, at least a little off-center, self-indulgent,
elitist.  ... It''s just good pedagogy, therefore, to stay away from such
stuff, and use instead, if film-strips and rap-sessions must be
supplemented, ''texts,'' selected, or prepared, or adapted, by real
professionals.  Those texts are called ''reading material.''  They are the
academic equivalent of the ''listening material'' that fills waiting-rooms,
and the ''eating material'' that you can buy in thousands of convenient eating
resource centers along the roads.
		-- The Underground Grammarian');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(569,'fortunes',84,'A bore is a man who talks so much about
himself that you can''t talk about yourself.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(570,'fortunes',96,'A bore is someone who persists in holding his
own views after we have enlightened him with ours.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(571,'fortunes',50,'A boss with no humor is like a job that''s no fun.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(572,'fortunes',91,'A box without hinges, key, or lid,
Yet golden treasure inside is hid.
		-- J. R. R. Tolkien');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(573,'fortunes',142,'A boy can learn a lot from a dog: obedience, loyalty, and the importance
of turning around three times before lying down.
		-- Robert Benchley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(574,'fortunes',64,'A boy gets to be a man when a man is needed.
		-- John Steinbeck');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(575,'fortunes',83,'A budget is just a method of worrying
before you spend money, as well as afterward.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(576,'fortunes',52,'A bug in the code is worth two in the documentation.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(577,'fortunes',55,'A bug in the hand is better than one as yet undetected.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(578,'fortunes',735,'A bunch of Polish scientists decided to flee their repressive government by
hijacking an airliner and forcing the pilot to fly them to the West.  They
drove to the airport, forced their way on board a large passenger jet, and
found there was no pilot on board.  Terrified, they listened as the sirens
got louder.  Finally, one of the scientists suggested that since he was an
experimentalist, he would try to fly the aircraft.
	He sat down at the controls and tried to figure them out.  The sirens
got louder and louder.  Armed men surrounded the jet.  The would be pilot''s
friends cried out, "Please, please take off now!!!  Hurry!!!"
	The experimentalist calmly replied, "Have patience.  I''m just a simple
pole in a complex plane."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(579,'fortunes',283,'A bunch of the boys were whooping it in the Malemute saloon;
The kid that handles the music box was hitting a jag-time tune;
Back of the bar, in a solo game, sat Dangerous Dan McGrew,
And watching his luck was his light-o''-love, the lady that''s known as Lou.
		-- Robert W. Service');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(580,'fortunes',100,'A bureaucrat''s idea of cleaning up his files
is to make a copy of everything before he destroys it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(581,'fortunes',72,'A businessman is a hybrid of a dancer and a calculator.
		-- Paul Valery');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(582,'fortunes',109,'A candidate is a person who gets money from the rich
and votes from the poor to protect them from each other.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(583,'fortunes',742,'A cannibal warrior is experiencing severe gastric distress, so he goes
to his Village Witch Doctor with his complaint.  The VWD examines him
and, concluding that something he ate disagreed with him, began to cross
examine him about his recent diet.
	"Well, I ate a missionary yesterday.  Do you think that could be
the problem?"
	The VWD says "Hmmmm."  (All doctors say "Hmmmm.")  "That could be.
Tell me a bit about this missionary."
	"Well, he was tall for a white man, wearing a brown robe.  He was
walking down the trail, not watching for danger, so I speared him, dragged
him home, cleaned him, boiled him and ate him."
	"Ah-hah!" (All doctors say "Ah-hah!")  There''s your problem," smiles
the VWD.  You boiled him, but he was a friar!"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(584,'fortunes',68,'A career is great, but you can''t run your fingers through its hair.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(585,'fortunes',513,'A castaway was washed ashore after many days on the open sea.  The island
on which he landed was populated by savage cannibals who tied him, dazed
and exhausted, to a thick stake.  They then proceeded to cut his arms
with their spears and drink his blood.  This continued for several days
until the castaway could stand no more.  He yelled for the cannibal chief
and declared, "You can kill me if you want to, but this torture with the
spears has got to stop.  Dammit, I''m tired of getting stuck for the drinks."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(586,'fortunes',107,'A casual stroll through a lunatic asylum shows that faith
does not prove anything.
		-- Friedrich Nietzsche');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(587,'fortunes',60,'A celebrity is a person who is known for his well-knownness.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(588,'fortunes',100,'A certain amount of opposition is a help, not a hindrance.
Kites rise against the wind, not with it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(589,'fortunes',786,'A certain monk had a habit of pestering the Grand Tortue (the only one who
had ever reached the Enlightenment ''Yond Enlightenment), by asking whether
various objects had Buddha-nature or not.  To such a question Tortue
invariably sat silent.  The monk had already asked about a bean, a lake,
and a moonlit night.  One day he brought to Tortue a piece of string, and
asked the same question.  In reply, the Grand Tortue grasped the loop
between his feet and, with a few simple manipulations, created a complex
string which he proffered wordlessly to the monk.  At that moment, the monk
was enlightened.

From then on, the monk did not bother Tortue.  Instead, he made string after
string by Tortue''s method; and he passed the method on to his own disciples,
who passed it on to theirs.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(590,'fortunes',995,'A certain old cat had made his home in the alley behind Gabe''s bar for some
time, subsisting on scraps and occasional handouts from the bartender.  One
evening, emboldened by hunger, the feline attempted to follow Gabe through
the back door.  Regrettably, only the his body had made it through when
the door slammed shut, severing the cat''s tail at its base.  This proved too
much for the old creature, who looked sadly at Gabe and expired on the spot.
	Gabe put the carcass back out in the alley and went back to business.
The mandatory closing time arrived and Gabe was in the process of locking up
after the last customers had gone.  Approaching the back door he was startled
to see an apparition of the old cat mournfully holding its severed tail out,
silently pleading for Gabe to put the tail back on its corpse so that it could
go on to the kitty afterworld complete.
	Gabe shook his head sadly and said to the ghost, "I can''t.  You know
the law -- no retailing spirits after 2:00 AM."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(591,'fortunes',590,'A Chicago salesman was about to check into a St. Louis hotel when he noticed
a very charming woman staring admiringly at him.  He walked over and spoke
with her for a few minutes, then returned to the front desk, where they checked
in as Mr. and Mrs.
	After a very pleasurable three-day stay, the man approached the front
desk and told the clerk he was checking out.  In a few minutes, he was handed
a bill for $2500.
	"There must be some mistake," the salesman said.  "I''ve been here for
only three days."
	"Yes, sir," the clerk replied.  "But your wife has been here a month
and a half."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(592,'fortunes',50,'A chicken is an egg''s way of producing more eggs.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(593,'fortunes',223,'A child can go only so far in life without potty training.  It is not mere
coincidence that six of the last seven presidents were potty trained, not
to mention nearly half of the nation''s state legislators.
		-- Dave Barry');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(594,'fortunes',65,'A child of five could understand this!  Fetch me a child of five.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(595,'fortunes',78,'A chronic disposition to inquiry
deprives domestic felines of vital qualities.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(596,'fortunes',99,'A chubby man with a white beard and a red suit
will approach you soon.  Avoid him.  He''s a Commie.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(597,'fortunes',143,'A citizen of America will cross the ocean to fight for democracy, but
won''t cross the street to vote in a national election.
		-- Bill Vaughan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(598,'fortunes',85,'A city is a large community where people are lonesome together.
		-- Herbert Prochnow');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(599,'fortunes',61,'A clash of doctrine is not a disaster - it is an opportunity.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(600,'fortunes',167,'A classic is something that everybody wants to have read
and nobody wants to read.
		-- Mark Twain quoting Professor Winchester,
		   "The Disappearance of Literature"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(601,'fortunes',47,'A clever prophet makes sure of the event first.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(602,'fortunes',342,'A cloud does not know why it moves in just such a direction and at such
a speed, if feels an impulsion... this is the place to go now.  But the
sky knows the reasons and the patterns behind all clouds, and you will
know, too, when you lift yourself high enough to see beyond horizons.
		-- Messiah''s Handbook: Reminders for the Advanced Soul');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(603,'fortunes',466,'A CODE OF ETHICAL BEHAVIOR FOR PATIENTS:

1. DO NOT EXPECT YOUR DOCTOR TO SHARE YOUR DISCOMFORT.
	Involvement with the patient''s suffering might cause him to lose
	valuable scientific objectivity.

2. BE CHEERFUL AT ALL TIMES.
	Your doctor leads a busy and trying life and requires all the
	gentleness and reassurance he can get.

3. TRY TO SUFFER FROM THE DISEASE FOR WHICH YOU ARE BEING TREATED.
	Remember that your doctor has a professional reputation to uphold.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(604,'fortunes',637,'A CODE OF ETHICAL BEHAVIOR FOR PATIENTS:

4. DO NOT COMPLAIN IF THE TREATMENT FAILS TO BRING RELIEF.
	You must believe that your doctor has achieved a deep insight into
	the true nature of your illness, which transcends any mere permanent
	disability you may have experienced.

5. NEVER ASK YOUR DOCTOR TO EXPLAIN WHAT HE IS DOING OR WHY HE IS DOING IT.
	It is presumptuous to assume that such profound matters could be
	explained in terms that you would understand.

6. SUBMIT TO NOVEL EXPERIMENTAL TREATMENT READILY.
	Though the surgery may not benefit you directly, the resulting
	research paper will surely be of widespread interest.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(605,'fortunes',712,'A CODE OF ETHICAL BEHAVIOR FOR PATIENTS:

7. PAY YOUR MEDICAL BILLS PROMPTLY AND WILLINGLY.
	You should consider it a privilege to contribute, however modestly,
	to the well-being of physicians and other humanitarians.

8. DO NOT SUFFER FROM AILMENTS THAT YOU CANNOT AFFORD.
	It is sheer arrogance to contract illnesses that are beyond your means.

9. NEVER REVEAL ANY OF THE SHORTCOMINGS THAT HAVE COME TO LIGHT IN THE COURSE
   OF TREATMENT BY YOUR DOCTOR.
	The patient-doctor relationship is a privileged one, and you have a
	sacred duty to protect him from exposure.

10. NEVER DIE WHILE IN YOUR DOCTOR''S PRESENCE OR UNDER HIS DIRECT CARE.
	This will only cause him needless inconvenience and embarrassment.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(606,'fortunes',262,'A Code of Honour: never approach a friend''s girlfriend or wife with mischief
as your goal.  There are too many women in the world to justify that sort of
dishonourable behaviour.  Unless she''s really attractive.
		-- Bruce J. Friedman, "Sex and the Lonely Guy"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(607,'fortunes',80,'A committee is a group that keeps the minutes and loses hours.
		-- Milton Berle');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(608,'fortunes',104,'A committee is a life form with six or more legs and no brain.
		-- Lazarus Long, "Time Enough For Love"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(609,'fortunes',136,'A committee takes root and grows, it flowers, wilts and dies,
scattering the seed from which other committees will bloom.
		-- Parkinson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(610,'fortunes',87,'A commune is where people join together to share their lack of wealth.
		-- R. Stallman');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(611,'fortunes',39,'A company is known by the men it keeps.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(612,'fortunes',96,'A complex system that works is invariably
found to have evolved from a simple system that works.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(613,'fortunes',70,'A compliment is something like a kiss through a veil.
		-- Victor Hugo');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(614,'fortunes',97,'[A computer is] like an Old Testament god, with a lot of rules and no mercy.
		-- Joseph Campbell');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(615,'fortunes',146,'A computer lets you make more mistakes faster than any other invention,
with the possible exceptions of handguns and Tequila.
		-- Mitch Ratcliffe');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(616,'fortunes',709,'A computer salesman visits a company president for the purpose of selling
the president one of the latest talking computers.
Salesman:	"This machine knows everything. I can ask it any question
		and it''ll give the correct answer.  Computer, what is the
		speed of light?"
Computer:	186,000 miles per second.
Salesman:	"Who was the first president of the United States?"
Computer:	George Washington.
President:	"I''m still not convinced. Let me ask a question.
		Where is my father?"
Computer:	Your father is fishing in Georgia.
President:	"Hah!! The computer is wrong. My father died over twenty
		years ago!"
Computer:	Your mother''s husband died 22 years ago. Your father just
		landed a twelve pound bass.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(617,'fortunes',861,'A computer science student and a practical hacker are discussing problems
the computer science student has run in to.

CS Student:	I have this singularly linked tail-queued list and I''m trying
		to make it O(1) to go backwards an item, instead of O(n)...
		What''s the best way to go about that?  Should I just use a
		cached hash of each item and put it into a sorted lookup
		table, and cache the hash of the last item in the current
		queue entry and then go to its place in the hash table and
		get the pointer value from there?
Hacker:		No, you should add an item to the structure named ''prev'' and
		make it point to the previous item.
CS Student:	But we already have a structure element with that identifier
		and structure elements must have unique names within that
		scope!
Hacker:		So call it ''previous''.

And then the CS Student was enlightened.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(618,'fortunes',239,'A computer science student on an exam:

	According to Shannon, information has entropy.  Entropy is just
	a mathematical trick to introduce temperature.  Consequently,
	information has temperature.  Hence there are hot news and cool
	news.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(619,'fortunes',69,'A computer scientist is someone who fixes things that aren''t broken.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(620,'fortunes',158,'A computer, to print out a fact,
Will divide, multiply, and subtract.
	But this output can be
	No more than debris,
If the input was short of exact.
		-- Gigo');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(621,'fortunes',99,'A computer without COBOL and Fortran is like a piece of chocolate
cake without ketchup and mustard.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(622,'fortunes',69,'A conclusion is simply the place where someone got tired of thinking.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(623,'fortunes',139,'A conference is a gathering of important people who singly can
do nothing but together can decide that nothing can be done.
		-- Fred Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(624,'fortunes',54,'A CONS is an object which cares.
		-- Bernie Greenberg');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(625,'fortunes',92,'A conservative is a man who is too cowardly to fight and too fat to run.
		-- Elbert Hubbard');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(626,'fortunes',106,'A conservative is a man
who believes that nothing should be done for the first time.
		-- Alfred E. Wiggam');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(627,'fortunes',110,'A conservative is a man
with two perfectly good legs who has never learned to walk.
		-- Franklin D. Roosevelt');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(628,'fortunes',123,'A consultant is a person who borrows your watch, tells you what time it
is, pockets the watch, and sends you a bill for it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(629,'fortunes',81,'A continuing flow of paper is sufficient to continue the flow of paper.
		-- Dyer');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(630,'fortunes',107,'A copy of the universe is not what is required of art; one of the
damned things is ample.
		-- Rebecca West');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(631,'fortunes',30,'A couch is as good as a chair.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(632,'fortunes',88,'A countryman between two lawyers is like a fish between two cats.
		-- Benjamin Franklin');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(633,'fortunes',838,'A couple of young fellers were fishing at their special pond off the
beaten track when out of the bushes jumped the Game Warden.  Immediately,
one of the boys threw his rod down and started running through the woods
like the proverbial bat out of hell, and hot on his heels ran the Game
Warden.  After about a half mile the fella stopped and stooped over with
his hands on his thighs, whooping and heaving to catch his breath as the
Game Warden finally caught up to him.
	"Let''s see yer fishin'' license, boy," the Warden gasped.  The
man pulled out his wallet and gave the Game Warden a valid fishing
license.
	"Well, son", snarled the Game Warden, "You must be about as dumb
as a box of rocks!  You didn''t have to run if you have a license!"
	"Yes, sir," replied his victim, "but, well, see, my friend back
there, he don''t have one!"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(634,'fortunes',196,'A cousin of mine once said about money,
money is always there but the pockets change;
it is not in the same pockets after a change,
and that is all there is to say about money.
		-- Gertrude Stein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(635,'fortunes',1182,'A cow is a completely automated milk-manufacturing machine. It is encased
in untanned leather and mounted on four vertical, movable supports, one at
each corner.  The front end of the machine, or input, contains the cutting
and grinding mechanism, utilizing a unique feedback device.  Here also are
the headlights, air inlet and exhaust, a bumper and a foghorn.
	At the rear, the machine carries the milk-dispensing equipment as
well as a built-in flyswatter and insect repeller.  The central portion
houses a hydro- chemical-conversion unit.  Briefly, this consists of four
fermentation and storage tanks connected in series by an intricate network
of flexible plumbing.  This assembly also contains the central heating plant
complete with automatic temperature controls, pumping station and main
ventilating system.  The waste disposal apparatus is located to the rear of
this central section.
	Cows are available fully-assembled in an assortment of sizes and
colors.  Production output ranges from 2 to 20 tons of milk per year.  In
brief, the main external visible features of the cow are:  two lookers, two
hookers, four stander-uppers, four hanger-downers, and a swishy-wishy.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(636,'fortunes',95,'A critic is a bundle of biases held loosely together by a sense of taste.
		-- Whitney Balliett');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(637,'fortunes',183,'A "critic" is a man who creates nothing and thereby feels
qualified to judge the work of creative men.  There is logic
in this; he is unbiased -- he hates all creative people equally.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(638,'fortunes',92,'A cynic is a person searching for an honest man, with a stolen lantern.
		-- Edgar A. Shoaff');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(639,'fortunes',40,'A day for firm decisions!!!!!  Or is it?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(640,'fortunes',62,'A day without orange juice is like a day without orange juice.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(641,'fortunes',58,'A day without sunshine is like a day without Anita Bryant.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(642,'fortunes',58,'A day without sunshine is like a day without orange juice.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(643,'fortunes',37,'A day without sunshine is like night.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(644,'fortunes',53,'A dead man cannot bite.
		-- Gnaeus Pompeius (Pompey)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(645,'fortunes',109,'A debugged program is one for which you have
not yet found the conditions that make it fail.
		-- Jerry Ogdin');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(646,'fortunes',458,'A decade after Vietnam, we still cannot understand why "their"
Salvadorans fight better than "our" Salvadorans.  It is not a matter of
their training or their equipment.  It has to do with the quality of the
society we are asking them to risk death defending.  The metaphor of the
domino obscures this reality, and the cost our self-imposed blindness
is high.  San Salvador is closer to Saigon than to Munich.
		-- William LeoGrande, "New York Times", 3/9/83');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(647,'fortunes',72,'A Difficulty for Every Solution.
		-- Motto of the Federal Civil Service');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(648,'fortunes',78,'A diplomat is a man who can convince his
wife she''d look stout in a fur coat.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(649,'fortunes',107,'A diplomat is a man who can tell you to
go to hell and make the trip sound pleasurable.
		-- Samuel Clemens');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(650,'fortunes',150,'A diplomat is a person who can tell you to go to hell
in such a way that you actually look forward to the trip.
		-- Caskie Stinnett, "Out of the Red"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(651,'fortunes',95,'A diplomat is man who always remembers a woman''s birthday but never her age.
		-- Robert Frost');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(652,'fortunes',118,'A diplomatic husband said to his wife, "How do you expect me to remember
your birthday when you never look any older?"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(653,'fortunes',100,'A diplomat''s life consists of three things: protocol, Geritol, and alcohol.
		-- Adlai E. Stevenson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(654,'fortunes',369,'A distraught patient phoned her doctor''s office.  "Was it true," the woman
inquired, "that the medication the doctor had prescribed was for the rest
of her life?"
	She was told that it was.  There was just a moment of silence before
the woman proceeded bravely on.  "Well, I''m wondering, then, how serious my
condition is.  This prescription is marked `NO REFILLS''".');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(655,'fortunes',71,'A diva who specializes in risqu''e arias is an off-coloratura soprano.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(656,'fortunes',338,'A doctor calls his patient to give him the results of his tests.  "I have
some bad news," says the doctor, "and some worse news."  The bad news is
that you only have six weeks to live."
	"Oh, no," says the patient.  "What could possibly be worse than
that?"
	"Well," the doctor replies, "I''ve been trying to reach you since
last Monday."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(657,'fortunes',246,'A doctor was stranded with a lawyer in a leaky life raft in shark-infested
waters. The doctor tried to swim ashore but was eaten by the sharks. The
lawyer, however, swam safely past the bloodthirsty sharks.  "Professional
courtesy," he explained.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(658,'fortunes',73,'A door is what a dog is perpetually on the wrong side of.
		-- Ogden Nash');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(659,'fortunes',104,'A drama critic is a person who surprises a playwright by informing him
what he meant.
		-- Wilson Mizner');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(660,'fortunes',89,'A dream will always triumph over reality, once it is given the chance.
		-- Stanislaw Lem');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(661,'fortunes',292,'A Dublin lawyer died in poverty and many barristers of the city subscribed to
a fund for his funeral.  The Lord Chief Justice of Orbury was asked to donate
a shilling.  "Only a shilling?" exclaimed the man. "Only a shilling to bury
an attorney?  Here''s a guinea; go and bury twenty of them."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(662,'fortunes',55,'A fail-safe circuit will destroy others.
		-- Klipstein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(663,'fortunes',67,'A failure will not appear until a unit has passed final inspection.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(664,'fortunes',64,'A fair exterior is a silent recommendation.
		-- Publilius Syrus');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(665,'fortunes',177,'A fake fortuneteller can be tolerated.  But an authentic soothsayer
should be shot on sight.  Cassandra did not get half the kicking around
she deserved.
		-- Robert A. Heinlein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(666,'fortunes',520,'A famous Lisp Hacker noticed an Undergraduate sitting in front of a Xerox
1108, trying to edit a complex Klone network via a browser.  Wanting to help,
the Hacker clicked one of the nodes in the network with the mouse, and asked
"what do you see?"  Very earnestly, the Undergraduate replied, "I see a
cursor."  The Hacker then quickly pressed the boot toggle at the back of
the keyboard, while simultaneously hitting the Undergraduate over the head
