In the Antartical Zonio.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1476,'fortunes',66,'Antonym, n.:
	The opposite of the word you''re trying to think of.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1477,'fortunes',515,'Anxious after the delay, Gruber doesn''t waste any time getting the Koenig
[a modified Porsche] up to speed, and almost immediately we are blowing off
Alfas, Fiats, and Lancias full of excited Italians.  These people love fast
cars.  But they love sport too and no passing encounter goes unchallenged.
Nothing serious, just two wheels into your lane as you''re bearing down on
them at 130-plus -- to see if you''re paying attention.
		-- Road & Track article about driving two absurdly fast
		   cars across Europe.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1478,'fortunes',153,'Any circuit design must contain at least one part which is obsolete, two parts
which are unobtainable, and three parts which are still under development.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1479,'fortunes',79,'Any clod can have the facts, but having opinions is an art.
		-- Charles McCabe');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1480,'fortunes',330,'Any coward can sit in his home and criticize a pilot for flying into a
mountain in a fog.  But I would rather, by far, die on a mountainside
than in bed.  What kind of man would live where there is no daring?
And is life so dear that we should blame men for dying in adventure?
Is there a better way to die?
		-- Charles Lindbergh');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1481,'fortunes',294,'Any dramatic series the producers want us to take seriously as a
representation of contemporary reality cannot be taken seriously as a
representation of anything -- except a show to be ignored by anyone
capable of sitting upright in a chair and chewing gum simultaneously.
		-- Richard Schickel');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1482,'fortunes',42,'Any excuse will serve a tyrant.
		-- Aesop');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1483,'fortunes',148,'Any father who thinks he''s all important should remind himself that this
country honors fathers only one day a year while pickles get a whole week.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1484,'fortunes',79,'Any fool can paint a picture, but it takes a
wise person to be able to sell it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1485,'fortunes',103,'Any fool can tell the truth, but it requires a man of sense to know
how to lie well.
		-- Samuel Butler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1486,'fortunes',94,'Any girl can be glamorous; all you have to do is stand still and look
stupid.
		-- Hedy Lamarr');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1487,'fortunes',45,'Any given program, when running, is obsolete.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1488,'fortunes',55,'Any given program will expand to fill available memory.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1489,'fortunes',317,'Any great truth can -- and eventually will -- be expressed as a cliche --
a cliche is a sure and certain way to dilute an idea.  For instance, my
grandmother used to say, "The black cat is always the last one off the
fence."  I have no idea what she meant, but at one time, it was undoubtedly
true.
		-- Solomon Short');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1490,'fortunes',71,'Any instrument when dropped will roll into the least accessible corner.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1491,'fortunes',272,'Any man can work when every stroke of his hand brings down the fruit
rattling from the tree to the ground; but to labor in season and out
of season, under every discouragement, by the power of truth -- that
requires a heroism which is transcendent.
		-- Henry Ward Beecher');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1492,'fortunes',85,'Any man who hates dogs and babies can''t be all bad.
		-- Leo Rosten, on W. C. Fields');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1493,'fortunes',204,'Any member introducing a dog into the Society''s premises shall be
liable to a fine of one pound.  Any animal leading a blind person shall
be deemed to be a cat.
		-- Rule 46, Oxford Union Society, London');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1494,'fortunes',81,'Any philosophy that can be put in a nutshell belongs there.
		-- Sydney J. Harris');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1495,'fortunes',134,'Any president should have the right to shoot
at least two people a year without explanation.
		-- Herbert Hoover, discussing the press');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1496,'fortunes',85,'Any priest or shaman must be presumed guilty until proved innocent.
		-- Lazarus Long');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1497,'fortunes',99,'Any problem in computer science can be solved with another layer
of indirection.
		-- David Wheeler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1498,'fortunes',41,'Any program which runs right is obsolete.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1499,'fortunes',74,'Any programming language is at its best before it is implemented and used.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1500,'fortunes',206,'Any road followed to its end leads precisely nowhere.
Climb the mountain just a little to test it''s a mountain.
From the top of the mountain, you cannot see the mountain.
		-- Bene Gesserit proverb, "Dune"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1501,'fortunes',78,'Any small object that is accidentally
dropped will hide under a larger object.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1502,'fortunes',124,'Any stone in your boot always migrates against the pressure gradient to
exactly the point of most pressure.
		-- Milt Barber');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1503,'fortunes',85,'Any sufficiently advanced bug is indistinguishable from a feature.
		-- Rich Kulawiec');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1504,'fortunes',77,'Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from a rigged demo.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1505,'fortunes',91,'Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.
		-- Arthur C. Clarke');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1506,'fortunes',115,'Any sufficiently simple directive can be obfuscated beyond reason
given proper legal counsel.
		-- Alfred Perlstein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1507,'fortunes',73,'Any time things appear to be going better, you have overlooked
something.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1508,'fortunes',100,'Any two philosophers can tell each other all they know in two hours.
		-- Oliver Wendell Holmes, Jr.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1509,'fortunes',59,'Anybody can win, unless there happens to be a second entry.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1510,'fortunes',156,'Anybody has a right to evade taxes if he can get away with it.  No citizen
has a moral obligation to assist in maintaining his government.
		-- J. P. Morgan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1511,'fortunes',159,'Anybody that wants the presidency so much that he''ll spend two years
organizing and campaigning for it is not to be trusted with the office.
		-- David Broder');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1512,'fortunes',83,'Anybody who doesn''t cut his speed at the
sight of a police car is probably parked.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1513,'fortunes',69,'Anybody with money to burn will easily find someone to tend the fire.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1514,'fortunes',198,'Anyone can become angry -- that is easy; but to be angry with the right
person, to the right degree, at the right time, for the right purpose
and in the right way -- that is not easy.
		-- Aristotle');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1515,'fortunes',123,'Anyone can do any amount of work provided it isn''t the work he is
supposed to be doing at the moment.
		-- Robert Benchley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1516,'fortunes',67,'Anyone can hold the helm when the sea is calm.
		-- Publilius Syrus');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1517,'fortunes',73,'Anyone can make an omelet with eggs.  The trick is to make one with
none.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1518,'fortunes',346,'Anyone can say "no." It is the first word a child learns and often the
first word he speaks. It is a cheap word because it requires no
explanation, and many men and women have acquired a reputation for
intelligence who know only this word and have used it in place of
thought on every occasion.
		-- Chuck Jones (Warner Bros. animation director.)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1519,'fortunes',67,'Anyone stupid enough to be caught by the police is probably guilty.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1520,'fortunes',114,'Anyone taking offence at fortune(s) is desperately lacking beer, in my
extremely humble opinion.
		-- Philip Paeps');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1521,'fortunes',208,'Anyone who cannot cope with mathematics is not fully human.  At best he
is a tolerable subhuman who has learned to wear shoes, bathe and not
make messes in the house.
		-- Lazarus Long, "Time Enough for Love"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1522,'fortunes',93,'Anyone who considers protocol unimportant has never dealt with a cat.
		-- Robert A. Heinlein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1523,'fortunes',135,'Anyone who describes Islam as a religion as intolerant encourages violence.
		-- Tasnim Aslam, Spokesman for Pakistani Foreign Ministry');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1524,'fortunes',86,'Anyone who goes to a psychiatrist ought to have his head examined.
		-- Samuel Goldwyn');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1525,'fortunes',290,'Anyone who has attended a USENIX conference in a fancy hotel can tell you
that a sentence like "You''re one of those computer people, aren''t you?"
is roughly equivalent to "Look, another amazingly mobile form of slime
mold!" in the mouth of a hotel cocktail waitress.
		-- Elizabeth Zwicky');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1526,'fortunes',109,'Anyone who has had a bull by the tail
knows five or six more things than someone who hasn''t.
		-- Mark Twain');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1527,'fortunes',133,'Anyone who imagines that all fruits ripen at the same time
as the strawberries, knows nothing about grapes.
		-- Philippus Paracelsus');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1528,'fortunes',165,'Anyone who is capable of getting themselves made President should on no
account be allowed to do the job.
		-- Douglas Adams, "The Hitchhiker''s Guide to the Galaxy"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1529,'fortunes',242,'Anyone who knows history, particularly the history of Europe, will, I think,
recognize that the domination of education or of government by any one
particular religious faith is never a happy arrangement for the people.
		-- Eleanor Roosevelt');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1530,'fortunes',76,'Anyone who says he can see through women is missing a lot.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1531,'fortunes',119,'Anyone who uses the phrase "easy as taking candy from a baby" has never
tried taking candy from a baby.
		-- Robin Hood');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1532,'fortunes',66,'Anything anybody can say about America is true.
		-- Emmett Grogan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1533,'fortunes',41,'Anything cut to length will be too short.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1534,'fortunes',43,'Anything free is worth what you pay for it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1535,'fortunes',55,'Anything is good and useful if it''s made of chocolate.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1536,'fortunes',46,'Anything is possible on paper.
		-- Ron McAfee');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1537,'fortunes',39,'Anything is possible, unless it''s not.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1538,'fortunes',166,'Anything labeled "NEW" and/or "IMPROVED" isn''t.
The label means the price went up.
The label "ALL NEW", "COMPLETELY NEW", or "GREAT NEW"
means the price went way up.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1539,'fortunes',54,'Anything that is good and useful is made of chocolate.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1540,'fortunes',159,'Anything that is worth doing has been done frequently.  Things hitherto
undone should be given, I suspect, a wide berth.
		-- Max Beerbohm, "Mainly on the Air"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1541,'fortunes',40,'Anything worth doing is worth overdoing.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1542,'fortunes',652,'Anyway, I keep picturing all these little kids playing some game in this
big field of rye and all.  Thousands of little kids, and nobody''s around --
nobody big, I mean -- except me.  And I''m standing on the edge of some crazy
cliff.  What I have to do, I have to catch everybody if they start to go
over the cliff -- I mean if they''re running and they don''t look where they''re
going I have to come out from somewhere and catch them.  That''s all I''d do
all day.  I''d just be the catcher in the rye.  I know it;  I know it''s crazy,
but that''s the only thing I''d really like to be.  I know it''s crazy.
		-- J. D. Salinger, "Catcher in the Rye"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1543,'fortunes',74,'Apathy Club meeting this Friday.
If you want to come, you''re not invited.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1544,'fortunes',46,'Apathy is not the problem, it''s the solution.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1545,'fortunes',105,'APHASIA:
	Loss of speech in social scientists when asked
	at parties, "But of what use is your research?"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1546,'fortunes',148,'Aphorism, n.:
	A concise, clever statement.
Afterism, n.:
	A concise, clever statement you don''t think of until too late.
		-- James Alexander Thom');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1547,'fortunes',30,'APL hackers do it in the quad.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1548,'fortunes',232,'APL is a mistake, carried through to perfection.  It is the language of the
future for the programming techniques of the past: it creates a new generation
of coding bums.
		-- Edsger W. Dijkstra, SIGPLAN Notices, Volume 17, Number 5');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1549,'fortunes',122,'APL is a natural extension of assembler language programming;
...and is best for educational purposes.
		-- Alan J. Perlis');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1550,'fortunes',104,'APL is a write-only language.  I can write programs
in APL, but I can''t read any of them.
		-- Roy Keir');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1551,'fortunes',43,'Appearances often are deceiving.
		-- Aesop');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1552,'fortunes',76,'APPENDIX:
	A portion of a book, for which nobody yet has discovered any use.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1553,'fortunes',111,'Applause, n.:
	The echo of a platitude from the mouth of a fool.
		-- Ambrose Bierce, "The Devil''s Dictionary"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1554,'fortunes',56,'April is the cruelest month...
		-- Thomas Stearns Eliot');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1555,'fortunes',135,'Aquadextrous, adj.:
	Possessing the ability to turn the bathtub
	faucet on and off with your toes.
		-- Rich Hall & Friends, "Sniglets"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1556,'fortunes',273,'AQUARIUS (Jan 20 - Feb 18)
	You have an inventive mind and are inclined to be progressive.
	You lie a great deal.  On the other hand, you are inclined to be
	careless and impractical, causing you to make the same mistakes over
	and over again.  People think you are stupid.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1557,'fortunes',275,'AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 to Feb. 18)
	A friend will step forward and confide in you about your breath.  Rely
	on your outgoing personality and winning smile to get you into a lot
	of trouble.  Be relaxed, things will change.  Look for a pink slip on
	payday.  Stop wetting your bed.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1558,'fortunes',315,'AQUARIUS (Jan.20 - Feb.18)
	You are the type of person who never has enough money to do what
	you want.  Don''t expect things to get any better today, either.
	As a matter of fact they might get worse.  Intensify your
	relationship with your bank and any friends you have who might be
	able to lend you a few bucks.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1559,'fortunes',436,'Aquavit is also considered useful for medicinal purposes, an essential
ingredient in what I was once told is the Norwegian cure for the common
cold.  You get a bottle, a poster bed, and the brightest colored stocking
cap you can find.  You put the cap on the post at the foot of the bed,
then get into bed and drink aquavit until you can''t see the cap.  I''ve
never tried this, but it sounds as though it should work.
		-- Peter Nelson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1560,'fortunes',111,'Arbitrary systems, pl.n.:
	Systems about which nothing general can be said, save "nothing
general can be said."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1561,'fortunes',63,'ARCHDUKE FERDINAND FOUND ALIVE --
    FIRST WORLD WAR A MISTAKE');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1562,'fortunes',15,'Are we not men?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1563,'fortunes',35,'Are we running light with overbyte?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1564,'fortunes',218,'Are Women Human?
In the year 584, in Lyon, France, 43 Catholic bishops and 20 men
representing other bishops, after a lengthy debate, took a vote.
The results were 32 yes, 31 no.  Women were declared human by one
vote.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1565,'fortunes',621,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	Are you sure you''re telling the truth?  Think hard.
	Does it make you happy to know you''re sending me to an early grave?
	If all your friends jumped off the cliff, would you jump too?
	Do you feel bad?  How do you think I feel?
	Aren''t you ashamed of yourself?
	Don''t you know any better?
	How could you be so stupid?
	If that''s the worst pain you''ll ever feel, you should be thankful.
	You can''t fool me.  I know what you''re thinking.
	If you can''t say anything nice, say nothing at all.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1566,'fortunes',548,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	Do as I say, not as I do.
	Do me a favour and don''t tell me about it.  I don''t want to know.
	What did you do *this* time?
	If it didn''t taste bad, it wouldn''t be good for you.
	When I was your age...
	I won''t love you if you keep doing that.
	Think of all the starving children in India.
	If there''s one thing I hate, it''s a liar.
	I''m going to kill you.
	Way to go, clumsy.
	If you don''t like it, you can lump it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1567,'fortunes',453,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	Go away.  You bother me.
	Why?  Because life is unfair.
	That''s a nice drawing.  What is it?
	Children should be seen and not heard.
	You''ll be the death of me.
	You''ll understand when you''re older.
	Because.
	Wipe that smile off your face.
	I don''t believe you.
	How many times have I told you to be careful?
	Just because.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1568,'fortunes',473,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	Good children always obey.
	Quit acting so childish.
	Boys don''t cry.
	If you keep making faces, someday it''ll freeze that way.
	Why do you have to know so much?
	This hurts me more than it hurts you.
	Why?  Because I''m bigger than you.
	Well, you''ve ruined everything.  Now are you happy?
	Oh, grow up.
	I''m only doing this because I love you.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1569,'fortunes',537,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	When are you going to grow up?
	I''m only doing this for your own good.
	Why are you crying?  Stop crying, or I''ll give you something to
		cry about.
	What''s wrong with you?
	Someday you''ll thank me for this.
	You''d lose your head if it weren''t attached.
	Don''t you have any sense at all?
	If you keep sucking your thumb, it''ll fall off.
	Why?  Because I said so.
	I hope you have a kid just like yourself.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1570,'fortunes',570,'Are you a parent?  Do you sometimes find yourself unsure as to what to
say in those awkward situations?  Worry no more...

	You wouldn''t understand.
	You ask too many questions.
	In order to be a man, you have to learn to follow orders.
	That''s for me to know and you to find out.
	Don''t let those bullies push you around.  Go in there and stick
		up for yourself.
	You''re acting too big for your britches.
	Well, you broke it.  Now are you satisfied?
	Wait till your father gets home.
	Bored?  If you''re bored, I''ve got some chores for you.
	Shape up or ship out.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1571,'fortunes',17,'Are you a turtle?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1572,'fortunes',43,'Are you making all this up as you go along?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1573,'fortunes',37,'Are you sure the back door is locked?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1574,'fortunes',118,'Argue for your limitations, and sure enough, they''re yours.
		-- Messiah''s Handbook: Reminders for the Advanced Soul');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1575,'fortunes',109,'Arguments are extremely vulgar, for everyone
in good society holds exactly the same opinion.
		-- Oscar Wilde');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1576,'fortunes',80,'Arguments with furniture are rarely productive.
		-- Kehlog Albran, "The Profit"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(1577,'fortunes',169,'ARIES (Mar 21 - Apr 19)
	You are the pioneer type and hold most people in contempt.  You are
	quick tempered, impatient, and scornful of advice.  You are not
