INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2981,'fortunes',35,'Everyone is entitled to my opinion.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2982,'fortunes',44,'Everyone is in the best seat.
		-- John Cage');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2983,'fortunes',63,'Everyone is more or less mad on one point.
		-- Rudyard Kipling');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2984,'fortunes',663,'Everyone knows that dragons don''t exist.  But while this simplistic
formulation may satisfy the layman, it does not suffice for the
scientific mind.  The School of Higher Neantical Nillity is in fact
wholly unconcerned with what _d_o_e_s exist.  Indeed, the banality of
existence has been so amply demonstrated, there is no need for us to
discuss it any further here.  The brilliant Cerebron, attacking the
problem analytically, discovered three distinct kinds of dragon: the
mythical, the chimerical, and the purely hypothetical.  They were all,
one might say, nonexistent, but each nonexisted in an entirely
different way ...
		-- Stanislaw Lem, "Cyberiad"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2985,'fortunes',71,'Everyone talks about apathy, but no one _d_o_e_s anything about it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(2986,'fortunes',95,'Everyone wants results, but no one is willing to do what it takes
