		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4271,'fortunes',476,'I got tired of listening to the recording on the phone at the movie
theater.  So I bought the album.  I got kicked out of a theater the
other day for bringing my own food in.  I argued that the concession
stand prices were outrageous.  Besides, I hadn''t had a barbecue in a
long time.  I went to the theater and the sign said adults $5 children
$2.50.  I told them I wanted 2 boys and a girl.  I once took a cab to
a drive-in movie.  The movie cost me $95.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4272,'fortunes',74,'I got vision, and the rest of the world wears bifocals.
		-- Butch Cassidy');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4273,'fortunes',451,'I GUESS I KINDA LOST CONTROL because in the middle of the play I ran up
and lit the evil puppet villain on fire.

No, I didn''t. Just kidding.  I just said that to illustrate one of the
human emotions which is freaking out.  Another emotion is greed, as when
you kill someone for money or something like that.  Another emotion is
generosity, as when you pay someone double what he paid for his stupid
puppet.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4274,'fortunes',246,'I GUESS I''LL NEVER FORGET HER.  And maybe I don''t want to.  Her spirit
was wild, like a wild monkey.  Her beauty was like a beautiful horse
being ridden by a wild monkey.  I forget her other qualities.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4275,'fortunes',185,'I guess I''ve been so wrapped up in playing the game that I never took
time enough to figure out where the goal line was -- what it meant to
win -- or even how you won.
		-- Cash McCall');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4276,'fortunes',125,'I guess I''ve been wrong all my life, but so have billions of
other people...  Certainty is just an emotion.
		-- Hal Clement');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4277,'fortunes',234,'I GUESS OF ALL MY UNCLES, I liked Uncle Caveman the best. We called him
Uncle Caveman because he lived in a cave and because sometimes he''d eat
one of us.  Later, we found out he was a bear.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4278,'fortunes',73,'I guess the Little League is even littler than we thought.
		-- D. Cavett');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4279,'fortunes',188,'I GUESS WE WERE ALL GUILTY, in a way.  We shot him, we skinned him, and
we all got a complimentary bumper sticker that said, "I helped skin Bob."
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4280,'fortunes',281,'I had a dream last night...
I dreamt about 1976.
I dreamt about a country with incurable brain damage...
I even dreamt they gave it a heart transplant.
Then I woke up and I knew it was only a nightmare...
so I went back to sleep again.
		-- Ralph Steadman, "Fear and Loathing ''72"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4281,'fortunes',421,'I had a feeling once about mathematics -- that I saw it all.  Depth beyond
depth was revealed to me -- the Byss and the Abyss. I saw -- as one might
see the transit of Venus or even the Lord Mayor''s Show -- a quantity passing
through infinity and changing its sign from plus to minus.  I saw exactly
why it happened and why tergiversation was inevitable -- but it was after
dinner and I let it go.
		-- Winston Churchill');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4282,'fortunes',170,'I had a virgin once.  I had to go to Guatemala for her.  She was blind
in one eye, and she had a stuffed alligator that said, "Welcome to Miami
Beach."
		-- The Stunt Man');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4283,'fortunes',183,'I had another dream the other day about government financial management
people.  They were small and rodent-like with padlocked ears, as if they
had stepped out of a painting by Goya.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4284,'fortunes',174,'I had another dream the other day about music critics.  They were small
and rodent-like with padlocked ears, as if they had stepped out of a
painting by Goya.
		-- Stravinsky');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4285,'fortunes',281,'I had never been too political, but I knew how white people treated black
people and it was hard for me to come back to the bullshit white people
put a black person through in this country.  To realize you don''t have any
power to make things different is a bitch.
		-- Miles Davis');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4286,'fortunes',107,'I had no shoes and I pitied myself.  Then I met a man who had no feet,
so I took his shoes.
		-- Dave Barry');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4287,'fortunes',113,'I had the rare misfortune of being one of the first people to try and
implement a PL/1 compiler.
		-- T. Cheatham');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4288,'fortunes',123,'I had to censor everything my sons watched ... even on the Mary Tyler
Moore show I heard the word "damn!"
		-- Mary Lou Bax');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4289,'fortunes',50,'I had to hit him -- he was starting to make sense.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4290,'fortunes',51,'I hate babies.  They''re so human.
		-- H. H. Munro');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4291,'fortunes',31,'I hate dying.
		-- Dave Johnson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4292,'fortunes',118,'I hate it when my foot falls asleep during the day cause that means
it''s going to be up all night.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4293,'fortunes',104,'I hate mankind, for I think myself one of the best of them,
and I know how bad I am.
		-- Samuel Johnson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4294,'fortunes',43,'I hate quotations.
		-- Ralph Waldo Emerson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4295,'fortunes',113,'I hate small towns because once you''ve seen the cannon in the park
there''s nothing else to do.
		-- Lenny Bruce');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4296,'fortunes',129,'I hate trolls.  Maybe I could metamorph it into something else -- like a
ravenous, two-headed, fire-breathing dragon.
		-- Willow');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4297,'fortunes',648,'I have a box of telephone rings under my bed.  Whenever I get lonely, I
open it up a little bit, and I get a phone call.  One day I dropped the
box all over the floor.  The phone wouldn''t stop ringing.  I had to get
it disconnected.  So I got a new phone.  I didn''t have much money, so I
had to get an irregular.  It doesn''t have a five.  I ran into a friend
of mine on the street the other day.  He said why don''t you give me a
call.  I told him I can''t call everybody I want to anymore, my phone
doesn''t have a five.  He asked how long had it been that way.  I said I
didn''t know -- my calendar doesn''t have any sevens.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4298,'fortunes',198,'I have a dog; I named him Stay.  So when I''d go to call him, I''d say, "Here,
Stay, here..." but he got wise to that.  Now when I call him he ignores me
and just keeps on typing.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4299,'fortunes',227,'I have a dream.  I have a dream that one day, on the red hills of Georgia,
the sons of former slaves and the sons of former slaveowners will be able to
sit down together at the table of brotherhood.
		-- Martin Luther King, Jr.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4300,'fortunes',198,'I have a friend whose a billionaire.  He invented Cliff''s notes.  When
I asked him how he got such a great idea he said, "Well first I...
I just... to make a long story short..."
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4301,'fortunes',128,'I have a hard time being attracted to anyone who can beat me up.
		-- John McGrath, Atlanta sportswriter, on women weightlifters');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4302,'fortunes',172,'I have a hobby.  I have the world''s largest collection of sea shells.
I keep it scattered on beaches all over the world.  Maybe you''ve seen
some of it.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4303,'fortunes',494,'I have a little shadow that goes in and out with me,
And what can be the use of him is more than I can see.
He is very, very like me from the heels up to the head;
And I see him jump before me, when I jump into my bed.

The funniest thing about him is the way he likes to grow--
Not at all like proper children, which is always very slow;
For he sometimes shoots up taller, like an india-rubber ball,
And he sometimes gets so little that there''s none of him at all.
		-- Robert Louis Stevenson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4304,'fortunes',150,'I have a map of the United States.  It''s actual size.
I spent last summer folding it.
People ask me where I live, and I say, "E6".
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4305,'fortunes',71,'I have a rock garden.  Last week three of them died.
		-- Richard Diran');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4306,'fortunes',216,'I have a switch in my apartment that doesn''t do anything.  Every once
in a while I turn it on and off.  On and off.  On and off.  One day I
got a call from a woman in France who said "Cut it out!"
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4307,'fortunes',75,'I have a terrible headache, I was putting on toilet water and the lid fell.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4308,'fortunes',79,'I have a theory that it''s impossible to prove anything,
but I can''t prove it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4309,'fortunes',79,'I have a very firm grasp on reality!  I can reach out and strangle it
any time!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4310,'fortunes',63,'I have a very strange feeling about this...
		-- Luke Skywalker');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4311,'fortunes',112,'I have already given two cousins to the war and I stand ready to
sacrifice my wife''s brother.
		-- Artemus Ward');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4312,'fortunes',132,'I have always noticed that whenever a radical takes
to Imperialism, he catches it in a very acute form.
		-- Winston Churchill, 1903');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4313,'fortunes',89,'I have an existential map.  It has "You are here" written all over it.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4314,'fortunes',36,'I have become me without my consent.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4315,'fortunes',176,'I have come up with a surefire concept for a hit television show, which
would be called "A Live Celebrity Gets Eaten by a Shark."
		-- Dave Barry, "The Wonders of Sharks on TV"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4316,'fortunes',103,'I have defined the hundred per cent American as ninety-nine per
cent an idiot.
		-- George Bernard Shaw');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4317,'fortunes',117,'I have discovered that all human evil comes from this, man''s being unable
to sit still in a room.
		-- Blaise Pascal');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4318,'fortunes',121,'I have discovered the art of deceiving diplomats.
I tell them the truth and they never believe me.
		-- Camillo Di Cavour');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4319,'fortunes',337,'I have found it impossible to carry the heavy burden of responsibility and
to discharge my duties as king as I would wish to do without the help and
support of the woman I love.
		-- Edward, Duke of Windsor, announcing his abdication
		   of the British throne in order to marry the American
		   divorcee Wallis Warfield Simpson. (1936)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4320,'fortunes',113,'I have found little that is good about human beings.  In my experience
most of them are trash.
		-- Sigmund Freud');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4321,'fortunes',124,'I have gained this by philosophy:
that I do without being commanded what others
do only from fear of the law.
		-- Aristotle');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4322,'fortunes',87,'I have great faith in fools -- self confidence my friends call it.
		-- Edgar Allan Poe');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4323,'fortunes',118,'I have had my television aerials removed.  It''s the moral equivalent
of a prostate operation.
		-- Malcolm Muggeridge');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4324,'fortunes',81,'I have hardly ever known a mathematician who was capable of reasoning.
		-- Plato');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4325,'fortunes',108,'I have just had eighteen whiskeys in a row.
I do believe that is a record.
		-- Dylan Thomas, his last words');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4326,'fortunes',472,'I have just read your lousy review buried in the back pages.  You
sound like a frustrated old man who never made a success, an
eight-ulcer man on a four-ulcer job, and all four ulcers working.  I
have never met you, but if I do you''ll need a new nose and plenty of
beefsteak and perhaps a supporter below.  Westbrook Pegler, a
guttersnipe, is a gentleman compared to you.  You can take that as more
of an insult than as a reflection on your ancestry.
		-- Harry S. Truman');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4327,'fortunes',123,'I have learned silence from the talkative,
toleration from the intolerant, and kindness from the unkind.
		-- Kahlil Gibran');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4328,'fortunes',105,'I have learned
To spell hors d''oeuvres
Which still grates on
Some people''s n''oeuvres.
		-- Warren Knox');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4329,'fortunes',205,'I have lots of things in my pockets;
None of them is worth anything.
Sociopolitical whines aside,
Gan you give me, gratis, free,
The price of half a gallon
Of Gallo extra bad
And most of the bus fare home.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4330,'fortunes',120,'I have made mistakes but I have never made the
mistake of claiming that I have never made one.
		-- James Gordon Bennett');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4331,'fortunes',104,'I have made this letter longer than usual
because I lack the time to make it shorter.
		-- Blaise Pascal');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4332,'fortunes',53,'I have more hit points that you can possible imagine.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4333,'fortunes',106,'I have more humility in my little finger than you have in your whole
_B_O_D_Y!
		-- from "Cerebus" #82');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4334,'fortunes',96,'I have never been one to sacrifice
my appetite on the altar of appearance.
		-- A. M. Readyhough');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4335,'fortunes',74,'I have never let my schooling interfere with my education.
		-- Mark Twain');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4336,'fortunes',306,'I have never seen anything fill up a vacuum so fast and still suck.
		-- Rob Pike, on X

Steve Jobs said two years ago that X is brain-damaged and it will be
gone in two years.  He was half right.
		-- Dennis M. Ritchie

Dennis Ritchie is twice as bright as Steve Jobs, and only half wrong.
		-- Jim Gettys');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4337,'fortunes',167,'I have never understood this liking for war.  It panders to instincts
already catered for within the scope of any respectable domestic
establishment.
		-- Alan Bennett');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4338,'fortunes',137,'I have no doubt that it is a part of the destiny of the human race,
in its gradual improvement, to leave off eating animals.
		-- Thoreau');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4339,'fortunes',149,'I have no doubt the Devil grins,
As seas of ink I spatter.
Ye gods, forgive my "literary" sins--
The other kind don''t matter.
		-- Robert W. Service');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4340,'fortunes',233,'I have no right, by anything I do or say, to demean a human being in his
own eyes.  What matters is not what I think of him; it is what he thinks
of himself.  To undermine a man''s self-respect is a sin.
		-- Antoine de Saint-Exupery');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4341,'fortunes',29,'I have not yet begun to byte!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4342,'fortunes',82,'I have nothing but utter contempt for the courts of this land.
		-- George Wallace');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4343,'fortunes',188,'I have now come to the conclusion never again to think of marrying,
and for this reason: I can never be satisfied with anyone who would
be blockhead enough to have me.
		-- Abraham Lincoln');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4344,'fortunes',82,'I have often looked at women and committed adultery in my heart.
		-- Jimmy Carter');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4345,'fortunes',72,'I have often regretted my speech, never my silence.
		-- Publilius Syrus');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4346,'fortunes',1778,'I have sacrificed time, health, and fortune, in the desire to complete these
Calculating Engines.  I have also declined several offers of great personal
advantage to myself.  But, notwithstanding the sacrifice of these advantages
for the purpose of maturing an engine of almost intellectual power, and
after expending from my own private fortune a larger sum than the government
of England has spent on that machine, the execution of which it only
commenced, I have received neither an acknowledgment of my labors, nor even
the offer of those honors or rewards which are allowed to fall within the
reach of men who devote themselves to purely scientific investigations...
	If the work upon which I have bestowed so much time and thought were
a mere triumph over mechanical difficulties, or simply curious, or if the
execution of such engines were of doubtful practicability or utility, some
justification might be found for the course which has been taken; but I
venture to assert that no mathematician who has a reputation to lose will
ever publicly express an opinion that such a machine would be useless if
made, and that no man distinguished as a civil engineer will venture to
declare the construction of such machinery impracticable...
	And at a period when the progress of physical science is obstructed
by that exhausting intellectual and manual labor, indispensable for its
advancement, which it is the object of the Analytical Engine to relieve, I
think the application of machinery in aid of the most complicated and abstruse
calculations can no longer be deemed unworthy of the attention of the country.
In fact, there is no reason why mental as well as bodily labor should not
be economized by the aid of machinery.
		-- Charles Babbage, "The Life of a Philosopher"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4347,'fortunes',101,'I have seen the future and it is just like the present, only longer.
		-- Kehlog Albran, "The Profit"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4348,'fortunes',60,'I have seen the Great Pretender and he is not what he seems.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4349,'fortunes',81,'I have that old biological urge,
I have that old irresistible surge,
I''m hungry.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4350,'fortunes',82,'I have the simplest tastes.  I am always satisfied with the best.
		-- Oscar Wilde');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4351,'fortunes',83,'I have to convince you, or at least snow you ...
		-- Prof. Romas Aleliunas, CS 435');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4352,'fortunes',87,'I have to think hard to name an interesting man who does not drink.
		-- Richard Burton');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4353,'fortunes',438,'I have travelled the length and breadth of this country, and have talked with
the best people in business administration.  I can assure you on the highest
authority that data processing is a fad and won''t last out the year.
		-- Editor in charge of business books at Prentice-Hall
		   publishers, responding to Karl V. Karlstrom (a junior
		   editor who had recommended a manuscript on the new
		   science of data processing), c. 1957');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4354,'fortunes',78,'I have ways of making money that you know nothing of.
		-- John D. Rockefeller');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4355,'fortunes',149,'I have yet to see any problem, however complicated, which, when looked
at in the right way, did not become still more complicated.
		-- Poul Anderson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4356,'fortunes',61,'I haven''t lost my mind -- it''s backed up on tape somewhere.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4357,'fortunes',56,'I haven''t lost my mind; I know exactly where I left it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4358,'fortunes',84,'I hear the sound that the machines make,
and feel my heart break, just for a moment.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4359,'fortunes',50,'I hear what you''re saying but I just don''t care.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4360,'fortunes',177,'I heard a definition of an intellectual, that I thought was very
interesting: a man who takes more words than are necessary to tell
more than he knows.
		-- Dwight D. Eisenhower');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4361,'fortunes',90,'I hold it, that a little rebellion, now and then, is a good thing...
		-- Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4362,'fortunes',491,'I hold your hand in mine, dear, I press it to my lips,
I take a healthy bite from your dainty fingertips,
My joy would be complete, dear, if you were only here,
But still I keep your hand as a precious souvenir.

The night you died I cut it off, I really don''t know why,
For now each time I kiss it I get bloodstains on my tie,
I''m sorry now I killed you, our love was something fine,
So until they come to get me I will hold your hand in mine.

		-- Tom Lehrer, "I Hold Your Hand In Mine"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4363,'fortunes',93,'I hope you''re not pretending to be evil while
secretly being good.  That would be dishonest.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4364,'fortunes',67,'I just asked myself... what would John DeLorean do?
		-- Raoul Duke');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4365,'fortunes',100,'I just ate a whole package of Sweet Tarts and a can of Coke.
I think I saw God.
		-- B. Hathrume Duk');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4366,'fortunes',329,'I just got off the phone with Sonny Barger [President of the Hell''s Angels].
He wants me to appear as a character witness for him at his murder trial
and said he''d be glad to appear as a character witness on my behalf if I
ever needed one.  Needless to say, I readily agreed.
		-- Thomas King Forcade, publisher of "High Times"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4367,'fortunes',100,'I just got out of the hospital after a
speed reading accident.  I hit a bookmark.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4368,'fortunes',94,'I just know I''m a better manager when I have Joe DiMaggio in center field.
		-- Casey Stengel');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4369,'fortunes',69,'I just need enough to tide me over until I need more.
		-- Bill Hoest');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4370,'fortunes',130,'I kissed my first girl and smoked my first cigarette on the same day.
I haven''t had time for tobacco since.
		-- Arturo Toscanini');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4371,'fortunes',67,'I knew her before she was a virgin.
		-- Oscar Levant, on Doris Day');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4372,'fortunes',91,'I *knew* I had some reason for not logging you off...
If I could just remember what it was.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4373,'fortunes',128,'I knew one thing: as soon as anyone said you didn''t need a gun, you''d better
take one along that worked.
		-- Raymond Chandler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4374,'fortunes',324,'I know if you been talkin'' you done said
just how surprised you wuz by the living dead.
You wuz surprised that they could understand you words
and never respond once to all the truth they heard.
But don''t you get square!
There ain''t no rule that says they got to care.
They can always swear they''re deaf, dumb and blind.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4375,'fortunes',54,'I know it all.  I just can''t remember it all at once.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4376,'fortunes',99,'I know not how I came into this,
shall I call it a dying life or a living death?
		-- St. Augustine');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4377,'fortunes',135,'I know not with what weapons World War III will be fought, but
World War IV will be fought with sticks and stones.
		-- Albert Einstein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4378,'fortunes',60,'I know on which side my bread is buttered.
		-- John Heywood');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4379,'fortunes',147,'I know the answer!  The answer lies within the heart of all mankind!
The answer is twelve?  I think I''m in the wrong building.
		-- Charles Schulz');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4380,'fortunes',172,'I know the disposition of women: when you will, they won''t; when
you won''t, they set their hearts upon you of their own inclination.
		-- Publius Terentius Afer (Terence)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4381,'fortunes',134,'I know what "custody" [of the children] means.  "Get even."  That''s all
custody means.  Get even with your old lady.
		-- Lenny Bruce');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4382,'fortunes',374,'I know what you''re thinking -- "Did he fire six shots or only five?"
Well, to tell you the truth, in all the excitement, I kind of lost track
myself.  But being this is a .44 Magnum, the most powerful handgun in the
world, and would blow your head clean off, you''ve got to ask yourself
one question: "Do I feel lucky?"  Well, do you, punk?
		-- Harry Callahan, badge #2211');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4383,'fortunes',145,'I know you believe you understand what you think this fortune says,
but I''m not sure you realize that what you are reading is not what
it means.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4384,'fortunes',121,'I know you think you thought you knew what you thought I said,
but I''m not sure you understood what you thought I meant.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4385,'fortunes',72,'I know you''re in search of yourself, I just haven''t seen you anywhere.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4386,'fortunes',276,'I lately lost a preposition;
It hid, I thought, beneath my chair
And angrily I cried, "Perdition!
Up from out of under there."

Correctness is my vade mecum,
And straggling phrases I abhor,
And yet I wondered, "What should he come
Up from out of under for?"
		-- Morris Bishop');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4387,'fortunes',710,'I lay my head on the railroad tracks,
Waitin'' for the double E.
The railroad don''t run no more.
Poor poor pitiful me.			[chorus]
	Poor poor pitiful me, poor poor pitiful me.
	These young girls won''t let me be,
	Lord have mercy on me!
	Woe is me!

Well, I met a girl, West Hollywood,
Well, I ain''t naming names.
But she really worked me over good,
She was just like Jesse James.
She really worked me over good,
She was a credit to her gender.
She put me through some changes, boy,
Sort of like a Waring blender.		[chorus]

I met a girl at the Rainbow Bar,
She asked me if I''d beat her.
She took me back to the Hyatt House,
I don''t want to talk about it.		[chorus]
		-- Warren Zevon, "Poor Poor Pitiful Me"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4388,'fortunes',115,'I learned to play guitar just to get the girls, and anyone who says they
didn''t is just lyin''!
		-- Willie Nelson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4389,'fortunes',68,'I like being single.  I''m always there when I need me.
		-- Art Leo');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4390,'fortunes',109,'I like myself, but I won''t say I''m as handsome as the bull
that kidnaped Europa.
		-- Marcus Tullius Cicero');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4391,'fortunes',78,'I like paying taxes.  With them I buy civilization.
		-- Oliver Wendell Holmes');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4392,'fortunes',266,'I like to believe that people in the long run are going to do more to
promote peace than our governments.  Indeed, I think that people want
peace so much that one of these days governments had better get out of
the way and let them have it.
		-- Dwight D. Eisenhower');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4393,'fortunes',66,'I like work; it fascinates me; I can sit and look at it for hours.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4394,'fortunes',64,'I like young girls.  Their stories are shorter.
		-- Tom McGuane');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4395,'fortunes',49,'I like your game but we have to change the rules.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4396,'fortunes',52,'I live the way I type; fast, with a lot of mistakes.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4397,'fortunes',124,'I loathe people who keep dogs.  They are cowards who haven''t got the guts
to bite people themselves.
		-- August Strindberg');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4398,'fortunes',122,'I look at life as being cruise director on the Titanic.
I may not get there, but I''m going first class.
		-- Art Buchwald');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4399,'fortunes',131,'I love being married.  It''s so great to find that one special
person you want to annoy for the rest of your life.
		-- Rita Rudner');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4400,'fortunes',98,'I love children.  Especially when they cry -- for then
someone takes them away.
		-- Nancy Mitford');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4401,'fortunes',98,'I love dogs, but I hate Chihuahuas.  A Chihuahua isn''t a dog.
It''s a rat with a thyroid problem.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4402,'fortunes',51,'I love mankind ... It''s people I hate.
		-- Schulz');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4403,'fortunes',74,'I love Mickey Mouse more than any woman I''ve ever known.
		-- Walt Disney');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4404,'fortunes',177,'I love Saturday morning cartoons, what classic humour!  This is what
entertainment is all about ... Idiots, explosives and falling anvils.
		-- Calvin and Hobbes, Bill Watterson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4405,'fortunes',78,'I love the smell of napalm in the morning.
		-- Robert Duval, "Apocalypse Now"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4406,'fortunes',109,'I love to eat them Smurfies
Smurfies what I love to eat
Bite they ugly heads off,
Nibble on they bluish feet.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4407,'fortunes',59,'I love treason but hate a traitor.
		-- Gaius Julius Caesar');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4408,'fortunes',97,'I love you more than anything in this world.  I don''t expect that will last.
		-- Elvis Costello');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4409,'fortunes',91,'I love you, not only for what you are,
but for what I am when I am with you.
		-- Roy Croft');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4410,'fortunes',201,'I loved her with a love thirsty and desperate. I felt that we two might
commit some act so atrocious that the world, seeing us, would find it
irresistible.
		-- Gene Wolfe, "The Shadow of the Torturer"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4411,'fortunes',58,'I married beneath me.  All women do.
		-- Lady Nancy Astor');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4412,'fortunes',178,'I may appear to be just sitting here like a bucket of tapioca, but
don''t let appearances fool you.  I''m approaching old age ... at the
speed of light.
		-- Prof. Cosmo Fishhawk');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4413,'fortunes',48,'I may be getting older, but I refuse to grow up!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4414,'fortunes',83,'I may kid around about drugs, but really, I take them seriously.
		-- Doctor Graper');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4415,'fortunes',84,'I may not be totally perfect, but parts of me are excellent.
		-- Ashleigh Brilliant');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4416,'fortunes',117,'I met a wonderful new man.  He''s fictional, but you can''t have everything.
		-- Cecelia, "The Purple Rose of Cairo"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4417,'fortunes',143,'I met my latest girl friend in a department store.  She was looking at
clothes, and I was putting Slinkys on the escalators.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4418,'fortunes',96,'I might have gone to West Point, but I was too proud to speak to a
congressman.
		-- Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4419,'fortunes',147,'I must Create a System, or be enslav''d by another Man''s;
I will not Reason and Compare; my business is to Create.
		-- William Blake, "Jerusalem"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4420,'fortunes',84,'I must get out of these wet clothes and into a dry Martini.
		-- Alexander Woollcott');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4421,'fortunes',137,'I must have a prodigious quantity of mind; it takes me as much as a
week sometimes to make it up.
		-- Mark Twain, "The Innocents Abroad"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4422,'fortunes',44,'I must have slipped a disk -- my pack hurts!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4423,'fortunes',843,'I myself have dreamed up a structure intermediate between Dyson spheres
and planets.  Build a ring 93 million miles in radius -- one Earth orbit
-- around the sun.  If we have the mass of Jupiter to work with, and if
we make it a thousand miles wide, we get a thickness of about a thousand
feet for the base.

And it has advantages.  The Ringworld will be much sturdier than a Dyson
sphere.  We can spin it on its axis for gravity.  A rotation speed of 770
m/s will give us a gravity of one Earth normal.  We wouldn''t even need to
roof it over.  Place walls one thousand miles high at each edge, facing the
sun.  Very little air will leak over the edges.

Lord knows the thing is roomy enough.  With three million times the surface
area of the Earth, it will be some time before anyone complains of the
crowding.
		-- Larry Niven, "Ringworld"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4424,'fortunes',73,'I need another lawyer like I need another hole in my head.
		-- Fratianno');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4425,'fortunes',163,'I needed the good will of the legislature of four states.  I formed the
legislative bodies with my own money.  I found that it was cheaper that
way.
		-- Jay Gould');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4426,'fortunes',146,'I never cheated an honest man, only rascals.  They wanted
something for nothing.  I gave them nothing for something.
		-- Joseph "Yellow Kid" Weil');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4427,'fortunes',128,'I never deny, I never contradict.  I sometimes forget.
		-- Benjamin Disraeli, British PM, on dealing with the
		   Royal Family');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4428,'fortunes',31,'I never did it that way before.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4429,'fortunes',108,'I never expected to see the day when girls would get sunburned in the
places they do today.
		-- Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4430,'fortunes',88,'I never failed to convince an audience that the best thing they
could do was to go away.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4431,'fortunes',82,'I never forget a face, but in your case I''ll make an exception.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4432,'fortunes',63,'I never killed a man that didn''t deserve it.
		-- Mickey Cohen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4433,'fortunes',66,'I never loved another person the way I loved myself.
		-- Mae West');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4434,'fortunes',92,'I never made a mistake in my life.
I thought I did once, but I was wrong.
		-- Lucy Van Pelt');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4435,'fortunes',90,'I never met a man I didn''t want to fight.
		-- Lyle Alzado, professional football lineman');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4436,'fortunes',48,'I never met a piece of chocolate I didn''t like.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4437,'fortunes',51,'I never pray before meals -- my mom''s a good cook.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4438,'fortunes',96,'I never said all Democrats were saloonkeepers;
what I said was all saloonkeepers were Democrats.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4439,'fortunes',418,'I never saw a purple cow
I never hope to see one
But I can tell you anyhow
I''d rather see than be one.
		-- Gellett Burgess

I''ve never seen a purple cow
I never hope to see one
But from the milk we''re getting now
There certainly must be one
		-- Ogden Nash

Ah, yes, I wrote "The Purple Cow"
I''m sorry now I wrote it
But I can tell you anyhow
I''ll kill you if you quote it.
		-- Gellett Burgess, many years later');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4440,'fortunes',76,'I never take work home with me; I always leave it in some bar along the way.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4441,'fortunes',66,'I never vote for anyone.  I always vote against.
		-- W. C. Fields');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4442,'fortunes',80,'I often quote myself; it adds spice to my conversation.
		-- George Bernard Shaw');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4443,'fortunes',55,'I only know what I read in the papers.
		-- Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4444,'fortunes',85,'I only touch base with reality on an as-needed basis!
		-- Royal Floyd Mengot (Klaus)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4445,'fortunes',520,'I opened the drawer of my little desk and a single letter fell out, a
letter from my mother, written in pencil, one of her last, with unfinished
words and an implicit sense of her departure.  It''s so curious: one can
resist tears and "behave" very well in the hardest hours of grief.  But
then someone makes you a friendly sign behind a window... or one notices
that a flower that was in bud only yesterday has suddenly blossomed... or
a letter slips from a drawer... and everything collapses.
		-- Letters From Colette');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4446,'fortunes',39,'I owe, I owe,
It''s off to work I go...');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4447,'fortunes',104,'I owe the government $3400 in taxes.  So I sent them two hammers and a
toilet seat.
		-- Michael McShane');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4448,'fortunes',43,'I owe the public nothing.
		-- J. P. Morgan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4449,'fortunes',500,'I place economy among the first and most important virtues, and public debt as
the greatest of dangers to be feared.  To preserve our independence, we must
not let our rulers load us with perpetual debt.  If we run into such debts, we
must be taxed in our meat and drink, in our necessities and in our comforts,
in our labor and in our amusements.  If we can prevent the government from
wasting the labor of the people, under the pretense of caring for them, they
will be happy.
		-- Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4450,'fortunes',446,'I played lead guitar in a band called The Federal Duck, which is the
kind of name that was popular in the ''60s as a result of controlled
substances being in widespread use.  Back then, there were no
restrictions, in terms of talent, on who could make an album, so we
made one, and it sounds like a group of people who have been given
powerful but unfamiliar instruments as a therapy for a degenerative
nerve disease.
		-- Dave Barry, "The Snake"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4451,'fortunes',190,'I pledge allegiance to the flag
of the United States of America
and to the republic for which it stands,
one nation,
indivisible,
with liberty
and justice for all.
		-- Francis Bellamy, 1892');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4452,'fortunes',68,'I poured spot remover on my dog.  Now he''s gone.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4453,'fortunes',55,'I predict that today will be remembered until tomorrow!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4454,'fortunes',97,'I prefer rogues to imbeciles because they sometimes take a rest.
		-- Alexandre Dumas the Younger');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4455,'fortunes',137,'I prefer the most unjust peace to the most righteous war.
		-- Cicero

Even peace may be purchased at too high a price.
		-- Poor Richard');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4456,'fortunes',95,'I profoundly believe it takes a lot of practice to become a moral slob.
		-- William F. Buckley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4457,'fortunes',152,'I put contact lenses in my dog''s eyes.  They had little pictures of cats
on them.  Then I took one out and he ran around in circles.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4458,'fortunes',432,'I put the shotgun in an Adidas bag and padded it out with four pairs of
tennis socks, not my style at all, but that was what I was aiming for:  If
they think you''re crude, go technical; if they think you''re technical, go
crude.  I''m a very technical boy.  So I decided to get as crude as possible.
These days, though, you have to be pretty technical before you can even
aspire to crudeness.
		-- William Gibson, "Johnny Mnemonic"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4459,'fortunes',77,'I put up my thumb... and it blotted out the planet Earth.
		-- Neil Armstrong');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4460,'fortunes',379,'I read a column by George Will that Scarface should be rated X because
parents were taking their children to see it.  So what?  Why should the
motion-picture industry be responsible for our morality?
	Dad says to Mom, "Honey, Scarface is in town."
	"What''s it about?"
	"Human scum who kill each other over cocaine deals."
	"Sounds great!  Let''s take the kids!"
		-- Ian Shoales');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4461,'fortunes',107,'I read Playboy for the same reason I read National Geographic.
To see the sights I''m never going to visit.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4462,'fortunes',89,'I read the newspaper avidly.  It is my one form of continuous fiction.
		-- Aneurin Bevan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4463,'fortunes',678,'I realize that the MX missile is none of our concern.  I realize that
the whole point of living in a democracy is that we pay professional
congresspersons to concern themselves with things like the MX missile
so we can be free to concern ourselves with getting hold of the
plumber.

But from time to time, I feel I must address major public issues such
as this, because in a free and open society, where the very future of
the world hinges on decisions made by our elected leaders, you never
win large cash journalism awards if you stick to the topics I usually
write about, such as nose-picking.
		-- Dave Barry, "At Last, the Ultimate Deterrent Against
		   Political Fallout"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4464,'fortunes',76,'I really had to act; ''cause I didn''t have any lines.
		-- Marilyn Chambers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4465,'fortunes',122,'I really hate this damned machine
I wish that they would sell it.
It never does quite what I want
But only what I tell it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4466,'fortunes',219,'I really look with commiseration over the great body of my fellow citizens
who, reading newspapers, live and die in the belief that they have known
something of what has been passing in their time.
		-- Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4467,'fortunes',227,'I recognize terror as the finest emotion and so I will try to terrorize the
reader.  But if I find that I cannot terrify, I will try to horrify, and if
I find that I cannot horrify, I''ll go for the gross-out.
		-- Stephen King');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4468,'fortunes',125,'I refuse to consign the whole male sex to the nursery.  I insist on
believing that some men are my equals.
		-- Brigid Brophy');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4469,'fortunes',57,'I refuse to have a battle of wits with an unarmed person.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4470,'fortunes',624,'I remember once being on a station platform in Cleveland at four in the
morning.  A black porter was carrying my bags, and as we were waiting for
the train to come in, he said to me: "Excuse me, Mr. Cooke, I don''t want to
invade your privacy, but I have a bet with a friend of mine.  Who composed
the opening theme music of `Omnibus''?  My friend said Virgil Thomson."  I
asked him, "What do you say?" He replied, "I say Aaron Copeland." I said,
"You''re right."  The porter said, "I knew Thomson doesn''t write counterpoint
that way."  I told that to a network president, and he was deeply unimpressed.
		-- Alistair Cooke');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4471,'fortunes',157,'I remember Ulysses well...  Left one day for the post office
to mail a letter, met a blonde named Circe on the streetcar,
and didn''t come back for 20 years.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4472,'fortunes',95,'I remember when legal used to mean lawful, now it means some
kind of loophole.
		-- Leo Kessler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4473,'fortunes',119,'I replaced the headlights on my car with strobe lights.  Now it
looks like I''m the only one moving.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4474,'fortunes',77,'I respect faith, but doubt is what gives you an education.
		-- Wilson Mizner');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4475,'fortunes',140,'I respect the institution of marriage.  I have always thought that every
woman should marry -- and no man.
		-- Benjamin Disraeli, "Lothair"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4476,'fortunes',427,'I reverently believe that the maker who made us all makes everything in New
England, but the weather.  I don''t know who makes that, but I think it must be
raw apprentices in the weather-clerks factory who experiment and learn how, in
New England, for board and clothes, and then are promoted to make weather for
countries that require a good article, and will take their custom elsewhere
if they don''t get it.
		-- Mark Twain');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4477,'fortunes',113,'I sat down beside her, said hello, offered to buy her a drink...
and then natural selection reared its ugly head.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4478,'fortunes',201,'I saw a man pursuing the Horizon,
''Round and round they sped.
I was disturbed at this,
I accosted the man,
"It is futile," I said.
"You can never--"
"You lie!" He cried,
and ran on.
		-- Stephen Crane');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4479,'fortunes',83,'I saw a subliminal advertising executive, but only for a second.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4480,'fortunes',154,'I saw Lassie.  It took me four shows to figure out why the hairy kid
never spoke. I mean, he could roll over and all that, but did that
deserve a series?"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4481,'fortunes',42,'I saw what you did and I know who you are.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4482,'fortunes',235,'I see a bad moon rising.
I see trouble on the way.
I see earthquakes and lightnin''
I see bad times today.
Don''t go ''round tonight,
It''s bound to take your life.
There''s a bad moon on the rise.
		-- J. C. Fogerty, "Bad Moon Rising"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4483,'fortunes',159,'I see a good deal of talk from Washington about lowering taxes.  I hope
they do get ''em lowered down enough so people can afford to pay ''em.
		-- Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4484,'fortunes',190,'I see the eigenvalue in thine eye,
I hear the tender tensor in thy sigh.
Bernoulli would have been content to die
Had he but known such _a-squared cos 2(phi)!
		-- Stanislaw Lem, "Cyberiad"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4485,'fortunes',248,'I see where we are starting to pay some attention to our neighbors to
the south.  We could never understand why Mexico wasn''t just crazy about
us; for we have always had their good will, and oil and minerals, at heart.
		-- The Best of Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4486,'fortunes',987,'I sent a letter to the fish,		I said it very loud and clear,
I told them, "This is what I wish."	I went and shouted in his ear.
The little fishes of the sea,		But he was very stiff and proud,
They sent an answer back to me.		He said "You needn''t shout so loud."
The little fishes'' answer was		And he was very proud and stiff,
"We cannot do it, sir, because..."	He said "I''ll go and wake them if..."
I sent a letter back to say		I took a kettle from the shelf,
It would be better to obey.		I went to wake them up myself.
But someone came to me and said		But when I found the door was locked
"The little fishes are in bed."		I pulled and pushed and kicked and
						knocked,
I said to him, and I said it plain	And when I found the door was shut,
"Then you must wake them up again."	I tried to turn the handle, But...

	"Is that all?" asked Alice.
	"That is all." said Humpty Dumpty. "Goodbye."
		-- Lewis Carroll,
		   "Through the Looking-Glass,
		   and What Alice Found There" (1871)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4487,'fortunes',690,'I sent a message to another time,
But as the days unwind -- this I just can''t believe,
I sent a message to another plane,
Maybe it''s all a game -- but this I just can''t conceive.
...
I met someone who looks at lot like you,
She does the things you do, but she is an IBM.
She''s only programmed to be very nice,
But she''s as cold as ice, whenever I get too near,
She tells me that she likes me very much,
But when I try to touch, she makes it all too clear.
...
I realize that it must seem so strange,
That time has rearranged, but time has the final word,
She knows I think of you, she reads my mind,
She tries to be unkind, she knows nothing of our world.
		-- ELO, "Yours Truly, 2095"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4488,'fortunes',201,'I shall come to you in the night and we shall see who is stronger --
a little girl who won''t eat her dinner or a great big man with cocaine
in his veins.
		-- Sigmund Freud, in a letter to his fiancee');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4489,'fortunes',264,'I shall give a propagandist reason for starting the war, no matter whether
it is plausible or not.  The victor will not be asked afterwards whether
he told the truth or not.  When starting and waging war it is not right
that matters, but victory.
		-- Adolf Hitler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4490,'fortunes',261,'I shot an arrow in to the air, and it stuck.
		-- graffito in Los Angeles

On a clear day,
U.C.L.A.
		-- graffito in San Francisco

There''s so much pollution in the air now that if it weren''t for our
lungs there''d be no place to put it all.
		-- Robert Orben');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4491,'fortunes',114,'I should have been a country-western singer.  After all, I''m older than
most western countries.
		-- George Burns');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4492,'fortunes',17,'I smell a wumpus.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4493,'fortunes',113,'I sold my memoirs of my love life to Parker
Brothers -- they''re going to make a game out of it.
		-- Woody Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4494,'fortunes',97,'I sometimes think that God, in creating man, somewhat overestimated his
ability.
		-- Oscar Wilde');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4495,'fortunes',182,'I steal.
		-- Sam Giancana, explaining his livelihood to his draft board

Easy.  I own Chicago.  I own Miami.  I own Las Vegas.
		-- Sam Giancana, when asked what he did for a living');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4496,'fortunes',73,'I stick my neck out for nobody.
		-- Humphrey Bogart, "Casablanca" (1942)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4497,'fortunes',246,'I stood on the leading edge,
The eastern seaboard at my feet.
"Jump!" said Yoko Ono
I''m too scared and good-looking, I cried.
Go on and give it a try,
Why prolong the agony, all men must die.
		-- Roger Waters, "The Pros and Cons of Hitchhiking"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4498,'fortunes',150,'I stopped believing in Santa Claus when I was six.  Mother took me to
see him in a department store and he asked for my autograph.
		-- Shirley Temple');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4499,'fortunes',61,'I suggest a new strategy, R2: let the Wookiee win.
		-- C-3PO');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4500,'fortunes',340,'I suggest you locate your hot tub outside your house, so it won''t do
too much damage if it catches fire or explodes.  First you decide which
direction your hot tub should face for maximum solar energy.  After
much trial and error, I have found that the best direction for a hot
tub to face is up.
		-- Dave Barry, "The Taming of the Screw"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4501,'fortunes',267,'I suppose I could collect my books and get on back to school,
Or steal my daddy''s cue and make a living out of playing pool,
Or find myself a rock ''n'' roll band,
That needs a helping hand,
Oh, Maggie I wish I''d never seen your face.
		-- Rod Stewart, "Maggie May"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4502,'fortunes',695,'I suppose some of the variation between Boston drivers and the rest of the
country is due to the progressive Massachusetts Driver Education Manual which
I happen to have in my top desk drawer.  Some of the Tips for Better Driving
are worth considering, to wit:

[110.13]:
	"When traveling on a one-way street, stay to the right, so as not
	to interfere with oncoming traffic."

[22.17b]:
	"Learning to change lanes takes time and patience.  The best
	recommendation that can be made is to go to a Celtics [basketball]
	game; study the fast break and then go out and practice it
	on the highway."

[41.16]:
	"Never bump a baby carriage out of a crosswalk unless the kid''s really
	asking for it."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4503,'fortunes',609,'I suppose some of the variation between Boston drivers and the rest of the
country is due to the progressive Massachusetts Driver Education Manual which
I happen to have in my top desk drawer.  Some of the Tips for Better Driving
are worth considering, to wit:

[131.16d]:
	"Directional signals are generally not used except during vehicle
	inspection; however, a left-turn signal is appropriate when making
	a U-turn on a divided highway."

[96.7b]:
	"When paying tolls, remember that it is necessary to release the
	quarter a full 3 seconds before passing the basket if you are
	traveling more than 60 MPH."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4504,'fortunes',728,'I suppose some of the variation between Boston drivers and the rest of the
country is due to the progressive Massachusetts Driver Education Manual which
I happen to have in my top desk drawer.  Some of the Tips for Better Driving
are worth considering, to wit:

[173.15b]:
	"When competing for a section of road or a parking space, remember
	that the vehicle in need of the most body work has the right-of-way."

[141.2a]:
	"Although it is altogether possible to fit a 6'' car into a 6''
	parking space, it is hardly ever possible to fit a 6'' car into
	a 5'' parking space."

[105.31]:
	"Teenage drivers believe that they are immortal, and drive accordingly.
	Nevertheless, you should avoid the temptation to prove them wrong."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4505,'fortunes',130,'I suppose that in a few hours I will sober up. That''s such a sad
thought. I think I''ll have a few more drinks to prepare myself.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4506,'fortunes',155,'I tell them to turn to the study of mathematics, for it
is only there that they might escape the lusts of the flesh.
		-- Thomas Mann, "The Magic Mountain"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4507,'fortunes',304,'I tell ya, drugs never worked out for me.  The first time I tried smoking
pot I didn''t know what I was doing.  I smoked half the joint, got the
munchies, and ate the other half.

Well, the first time I tried coke I was so embarrassed.  I kept getting the
bottle stuck up my nose.
		-- Rodney Dangerfield');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4508,'fortunes',341,'I tell ya, gambling never agreed with me.  Last week I went to the track
and they shot my horse with the opening gun.

Well, just last week I was at a Chinese restaurant and when I opened my
fortune cookie I found the guy''s check sitting at the next table.  I said,
"Hey, buddy, I got your check", he said, "Thanks."
		-- Rodney Dangerfield');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4509,'fortunes',218,'I tell ya, I knew my morning wasn''t going right.   When I put on my shirt
the button fell off, when I picked up my briefcase, the handle fell off,
I tell ya, I was afraid to go to the bathroom.
		-- Rodney Dangerfield');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4510,'fortunes',91,'I think...  I think it''s in my basement... Let me go upstairs and check.
		-- M. C. Escher');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4511,'fortunes',158,'I think a relationship is like a shark.  It has to constantly move forward
or it dies.  Well, what we have on our hands here is a dead shark.
		-- Woody Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4512,'fortunes',62,'I think I''ll snatch a kiss and flee.
		-- William Shakespeare');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4513,'fortunes',93,'I think I''m schizophrenic.  One half of me''s
paranoid and the other half''s out to get him.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4514,'fortunes',139,'I think it is true for all _n. I was just playing it safe with _n >= 3
because I couldn''t remember the proof.
		-- Baker, Pure Math 351a');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4515,'fortunes',84,'I THINK MAN INVENTED THE CAR by instinct.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4516,'fortunes',56,'I think sex is better than logic, but I can''t prove it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4517,'fortunes',168,'I think she must have been very strictly brought up, she''s so
desperately anxious to do the wrong thing correctly.
		-- H. H. Munro, a.k.a. Saki, "Reginald on Worries"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4518,'fortunes',352,'I think that all good, right thinking people in this country are sick
and tired of being told that all good, right thinking people in this
country are fed up with being told that all good, right thinking people
in this country are fed up with being sick and tired.  I''m certainly
not, and I''m sick and tired of being told that I am.
		-- Monty Python');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4519,'fortunes',258,'I think that I shall never hear
A poem lovelier than beer.
The stuff that Joe''s Bar has on tap,
With golden base and snowy cap.
The stuff that I can drink all day
Until my mem''ry melts away.
Poems are made by fools, I fear
But only Schlitz can make a beer.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4520,'fortunes',142,'I think that I shall never see
A billboard lovely as a tree.
Indeed, unless the billboards fall
I''ll never see a tree at all.
		-- Ogden Nash');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4521,'fortunes',281,'I think that I shall never see
A thing as lovely as a tree.
But as you see the trees have gone
They went this morning with the dawn.
A logging firm from out of town
Came and chopped the trees all down.
But I will trick those dirty skunks
And write a brand new poem called "Trunks."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4522,'fortunes',660,'I think the sky is blue because it''s a shift from black through purple
to blue, and it has to do with where the light is.  You know, the
farther we get into darkness, and there''s a shifting of color of light
into the blueness, and I think as you go farther and farther away from
the reflected light we have from the sun or the light that''s bouncing
off this earth, uh, the darker it gets ... I think if you look at the
color scale, you start at black, move it through purple, move it on
out, it''s the shifting of color.  We mentioned before about the stars
singing, and that''s one of the effects of the shifting of colors.
		-- Pat Robertson, The 700 Club');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4523,'fortunes',142,'I think the world is ready for the story of an ugly duckling, who grew up to
remain an ugly duckling, and lived happily ever after.
		-- Chick');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4524,'fortunes',55,'I think the world is run by C students.
		-- Al McGuire');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4525,'fortunes',137,'I think the world would be a more peaceful place if people
could just keep their fingers out of the fortune files.
		-- Jordan K. Hubbard');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4526,'fortunes',275,'I THINK THERE SHOULD BE SOMETHING in science called the "reindeer effect."
I don''t know what it would be, but I think it''d be good to hear someone
say, "Gentlemen, what we have here is a terrifying example of the reindeer
effect."
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4527,'fortunes',35,'I think, therefore I am... I think.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4528,'fortunes',120,'I think there''s a world market for about five computers.
		-- attr. Thomas J. Watson, Chairman of the Board, IBM (1943)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4529,'fortunes',124,'I THINK THEY SHOULD CONTINUE the policy of not giving a Nobel Prize for
paneling.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4530,'fortunes',82,'I think we are in Rats Alley where the dead men lost their bones.
		-- T. S. Eliot');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4531,'fortunes',620,'I think we can all agree that there is not enough common courtesy shown
... HEY!  PAY ATTENTION WHEN I''M TALKING TO YOU DAMMIT!  I said I think
we can all agree that there is not enough common courtesy shown today.
When we take the time to be courteous to each other, we find that we
are happier and less likely to engage in nuclear war.  This point was
driven home by the recent summit talks, where Nancy Reagan and Raisa
Gorbachev, each of whose husband thinks the other''s husband is vermin,
were able to sit down at a high-level tea and engage in courteous
conversation ...
		-- Dave Barry, "The Stuff of Etiquette"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4532,'fortunes',63,'I think we''re all Bozos on this bus.
		-- The Firesign Theatre');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4533,'fortunes',40,'I think we''re in trouble.
		-- Han Solo');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4534,'fortunes',133,'I think your opinions are reasonable,
except for the one about my mental instability.
		-- Psychology Professor, Fairfield University');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4535,'fortunes',954,'"I thought that you said you were 20 years old!"
"As a programmer, yes," she replied,
"And you claimed to be very near two meters tall!"
"You said you were blonde, but you lied!"
Oh, she was a hacker and he was one, too,
They had so much in common, you''d say.
They exchanged jokes and poems, and clever new hacks,
And prompts that were cute or risque''.
He sent her a picture of his brother Sam,
She sent one from some past high school day,
And it might have gone on for the rest of their lives,
If they hadn''t met in L.A.
"Your beard is an armpit," she said in disgust.
He answered, "Your armpit''s a beard!"
And they chorused: "I think I could stand all the rest
If you were not so totally weird!"
If she had not said what he wanted to hear,
And he had not done just the same,
They''d have been far more honest, and never have met,
And would not have had fun with the game.
		-- Judith Schrier,
		   "Face to Face After Six Months of Electronic Mail"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4536,'fortunes',164,'I thought there was something fishy about the butler.  Probably a Pisces,
working for scale.
		-- The Firesign Theatre,
		   "The Further Adventures of Nick Danger"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4537,'fortunes',33,'I thought YOU silenced the guard!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4538,'fortunes',135,'I told my doctor I got all the exercise I needed being a
pallbearer for all my friends who run and do exercises!
		-- Winston Churchill');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4539,'fortunes',189,'I took a course in speed reading, learning to read straight down the middle
of the page, and I was able to go through "War and Peace" in twenty minutes.
It''s about Russia.
		-- Woody Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4540,'fortunes',178,'I treasure this strange combination found in very few persons: a fierce
desire for life as well as a lucid perception of the ultimate futility of
the quest.
		-- Madeleine Gobeil');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4541,'fortunes',227,'I truly wish I could be a great surgeon or philosopher or author or anything
constructive, but in all honesty I''d rather turn up my amplifier full blast
and drown myself in the noise.
		-- Charles Schmid, the "Tucson Murderer"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4542,'fortunes',96,'I trust the first lion he meets will do his duty.
		-- J. P. Morgan on Teddy Roosevelt''s safari');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4543,'fortunes',81,'I try not to break the rules but merely to test their elasticity.
		-- Bill Veeck');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4544,'fortunes',95,'I try to keep an open mind, but not so open that my brains fall out.
		-- Judge Harold T. Stone');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4545,'fortunes',397,'I turned my air conditioner the other way around, and it got cold out.
The weatherman said "I don''t understand it.  I was supposed to be 80
degrees today," and I said "Oops."

In my house on the ceilings I have paintings of the rooms above... so
I never have to go upstairs.

I just bought a microwave fireplace... You can spend an evening in
front of it in only eight minutes.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4546,'fortunes',82,'I understand why you''re confused.  You''re thinking too much.
		-- Carole Wallach');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4547,'fortunes',93,'I use not only all the brains I have, but all those I can borrow as well.
		-- Woodrow Wilson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4548,'fortunes',70,'I use technology in order to hate it more properly.
		-- Nam June Paik');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4549,'fortunes',432,'I used to be a rebel in my youth.
This cause... that cause... (chuckle) I backed ''em ALL!  But I learned.
Rebellion is simply a device used by the immature to hide from his own
problems.  So I lost interest in politics.  Now when I feel aroused by
a civil rights case or a passport hearing... I realize it''s just a device.
I go to my analyst and we work it out.  You have no idea how much better
I feel these days.
		-- J. Feiffer');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4550,'fortunes',51,'I used to be an agnostic, but now I''m not so sure.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4551,'fortunes',72,'I used to be disgusted, now I find I''m just amused.
		-- Elvis Costello');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4552,'fortunes',53,'I used to be Snow White, but I drifted.
		-- Mae West');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4553,'fortunes',718,'I used to be such a sweet sweet thing, ''til they got a hold of me,
I opened doors for little old ladies, I helped the blind to see,
I got no friends ''cause they read the papers, they can''t be seen,
With me, and I''m feelin'' real shot down,
And I''m, uh, feelin'' mean,
	No more, Mr. Nice Guy,
	No more, Mr. Clean,
	No more, Mr. Nice Guy,
They say "He''s sick, he''s obscene".

My dog bit me on the leg today, my cat clawed my eyes,
Ma''s been thrown out of the social circle, and Dad has to hide,
I went to church, incognito, when everybody rose,
The reverend Smithy, he recognized me,
And punched me in the nose, he said,
(chorus)
He said "You''re sick, you''re obscene".
		-- Alice Cooper, "No More Mr. Nice Guy"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4554,'fortunes',56,'I used to have a drinking problem.
Now I love the stuff.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4555,'fortunes',512,'I used to live in a house by the freeway.  When I went anywhere, I had
to be going 65 MPH by the end of my driveway.

I replaced the headlights in my car with strobe lights.  Now it looks
like I''m the only one moving.

I was pulled over for speeding today.  The officer said, "Don''t you know
the speed limit is 55 miles an hour?"  And I said, "Yes, but I wasn''t going
to be out that long."

I put a new engine in my car, but didn''t take the old one out.  Now
my car goes 500 miles an hour.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4556,'fortunes',165,'I used to think I was a child; now I think I am an adult -- not because
I no longer do childish things, but because those I call adults are no
more mature than I am.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4557,'fortunes',59,'I used to think I was indecisive, but now I''m not so sure.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4558,'fortunes',230,'I used to think romantic love was a neurosis shared by two, a supreme
foolishness.  I no longer thought that.  There''s nothing foolish in
loving anyone.  Thinking you''ll be loved in return is what''s foolish.
		-- Rita Mae Brown');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4559,'fortunes',131,'I used to think that the brain was the most wonderful organ in
my body.  Then I realized who was telling me this.
		-- Emo Phillips');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4560,'fortunes',105,'I used to work in a fire hydrant factory.  You couldn''t park anywhere near
the place.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4561,'fortunes',329,'I value kindness to human beings first of all, and kindness to animals.  I
don''t respect the law; I have a total irreverence for anything connected
with society except that which makes the roads safer, the beer stronger,
the food cheaper, and old men and women warmer in the winter, and happier
in the summer.
		-- Brendan Behan');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4562,'fortunes',72,'I waited and waited and when no message came I knew it must be from you.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4563,'fortunes',91,'I want to be the white man''s brother, not his brother-in-law.
		-- Martin Luther King, Jr.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4564,'fortunes',186,'I want to buy a husband who, every week when I sit down to watch "St.
Elsewhere", won''t scream, "FORGET IT, BLANCHE ... IT''S TIME FOR ''HEE
HAW''!!"
		-- Berke Breathed, "Bloom County"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4565,'fortunes',79,'I want to marry a girl just like the girl that married dear old dad.
		-- Freud');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4566,'fortunes',59,'I want to reach your mind -- where is it currently located?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4567,'fortunes',472,'I was appalled by this story of the destruction of a member of a valued
endangered species.  It''s all very well to celebrate the practicality of
pigs by ennobling the porcine sibling who constructed his home out of
bricks and mortar.  But to wantonly destroy a wolf, even one with an
excessive taste for porkers, is unconscionable in these ecologically
critical times when both man and his domestic beasts continue to maraud
the earth.
		Sylvia Kamerman, "Book Reviewing"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4568,'fortunes',127,'I was at this restaurant.  The sign said "Breakfast Anytime."  So I
ordered French Toast in the Renaissance.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4569,'fortunes',231,'I was born because it was a habit in those days, people didn''t know
anything else ... I was not a Child Prodigy, because a Child Prodigy is
a child who knows as much when it is a child as it does when it grows
up.
		-- Will Rogers');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4570,'fortunes',178,'I was born in a barrel of butcher knives
Trouble I love and peace I despise
Wild horses kicked me in my side
Then a rattlesnake bit me and he walked off and died.
		-- Bo Diddley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4571,'fortunes',321,'I was drunk last night, crawled home across the lawn.  By accident I
put the car key in the door lock.  The house started up.  So I figured
what the hell, and drove it around the block a few times.  I thought I
should go park it in the middle of the freeway and yell at everyone to
get off my driveway.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4572,'fortunes',233,'I was eatin'' some chop suey,
With a lady in St. Louie,
When there sudden comes a knockin'' at the door.
And that knocker, he says, "Honey,
Roll this rocker out some money,
Or your daddy shoots a baddie to the floor."
		-- Mr. Miggle');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4573,'fortunes',96,'I was gratified to be able to answer promptly, and I did.
I said I didn''t know.
		-- Mark Twain');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4574,'fortunes',515,'I was in a bar and I walked up to a beautiful woman and said, "Do you live
around here often?"  She said, "You''re wearing two different-color socks."
I said, "Yes, but to me they''re the same because I go by thickness."
She said, "How do you feel?" And I said, "You know when you''re sitting on a
chair and you lean back so you''re just on two legs and you lean too far so
you almost fall over but at the last second you catch yourself?  I feel like
that all the time."
		-- Steven Wright, "Gentlemen''s Quarterly"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4575,'fortunes',122,'I was in a beauty contest once.  I not only came in last, I was hit in
the mouth by Miss Congeniality.
		-- Phyllis Diller');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4576,'fortunes',101,'I was in accord with the system so long as it
permitted me to function effectively.
		-- Albert Speer');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4577,'fortunes',364,'I was in this prematurely air conditioned supermarket and there were all
these aisles and there were these bathing caps you could buy that had these
kind of Fourth of July plumes on them that were red and yellow and blue and
I wasn''t tempted to buy one but I was reminded of the fact that I had been
avoiding the beach.
		-- Lucinda Childs "Einstein On The Beach"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4578,'fortunes',138,'I was in Vegas last week. I was at the roulette table, having a
lengthy argument about what I considered an Odd number.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4579,'fortunes',782,'I was offered a job as a hoodlum and I turned it down cold.  A thief is
anybody who gets out and works for his living, like robbing a bank or
breaking into a place and stealing stuff, or kidnaping somebody.  He really
gives some effort to it.  A hoodlum is a pretty lousy sort of scum.  He
works for gangsters and bumps guys off when they have been put on the spot.
Why, after I''d made my rep, some of the Chicago Syndicate wanted me to work
for them as a hood -- you know, handling a machine gun.  They offered me
two hundred and fifty dollars a week and all the protection I needed.  I
was on the lam at the time and not able to work at my regular line.  But
I wouldn''t consider it.  "I''m a thief," I said.  "I''m no lousy hoodlum."
		-- Alvin Karpis, "Public Enemy Number One"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4580,'fortunes',226,'I was part of that strange race of people aptly described as spending
their lives doing things they detest to make money they don''t want to
buy things they don''t need to impress people they dislike.
		-- Emile Henry Gauvreay');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4581,'fortunes',117,'I was playing poker the other night... with Tarot cards.  I got a
full house and four people died.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4582,'fortunes',43,'I was the best I ever had.
		-- Woody Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4583,'fortunes',51,'I was toilet-trained at gunpoint.
		-- Billy Braver');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4584,'fortunes',348,'I was working on a case.  It had to be a case, because I couldn''t afford a
desk.  Then I saw her.  This tall blond lady.  She must have been tall
because I was on the third floor.  She rolled her deep blue eyes towards
me.  I picked them up and rolled them back.  We kissed.  She screamed.  I
took the cigarette from my mouth and kissed her again.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4585,'fortunes',69,'I wasn''t kissing her, I was whispering in her mouth.
		-- Chico Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4586,'fortunes',93,'I watch television because you don''t know what it will do if you leave it
in the room alone.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4587,'fortunes',251,'I went home with a waitress,
The way I always do.
How I was I to know?
She was with the Russians too.

I was gambling in Havana,
I took a little risk.
Send lawyers, guns, and money,
Dad, get me out of this.
		-- Warren Zevon, "Lawyers, Guns and Money"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4588,'fortunes',92,'I went into a general store ... they wouldn''t sell me anything specific.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4589,'fortunes',167,'I went into the business for the money, and the art grew out of it.
If people are disillusioned by that remark, I can''t help it.
It''s the truth.
		-- Charlie Chaplin');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4590,'fortunes',751,'I went on to test the program in every way I could devise.  I strained it to
expose its weaknesses.  I ran it for high-mass stars and low-mass stars, for
stars born exceedingly hot and those born relatively cold.  I ran it assuming
the superfluid currents beneath the crust to be absent -- not because I wanted
to know the answer, but because I had developed an intuitive feel for the
answer in this particular case.  Finally I got a run in which the computer
showed the pulsar''s temperature to be less than absolute zero.  I had found
an error.  I chased down the error and fixed it.  Now I had improved the
program to the point where it would not run at all.
		-- George Greenstein, "Frozen Star:
		   Of Pulsars, Black Holes and the Fate of Stars"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4591,'fortunes',223,'I went over to my friend, he was eatin'' a pickle.
I said "Hi, what''s happenin''?"
He said "Nothin''."
Try to sing this song with that kind of enthusiasm;
As if you just squashed a cop.
		-- Arlo Guthrie, "Motorcycle Song"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4592,'fortunes',94,'I went to a Grateful Dead Concert and they played for SEVEN hours.
Great song.
		-- Fred Reuss');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4593,'fortunes',317,'I went to a job interview the other day, the guy asked me if I had any
questions, I said yes, just one, if you''re in a car traveling at the
speed of light and you turn your headlights on, does anything happen?

He said he couldn''t answer that, I told him sorry, but I couldn''t work
for him then.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4594,'fortunes',489,'I went to my first computer conference at the New York Hilton about 20
years ago.  When somebody there predicted the market for microprocessors
would eventually be in the millions, someone else said, "Where are they
all going to go? It''s not like you need a computer in every doorknob!"

Years later, I went back to the same hotel.  I noticed the room keys had
been replaced by electronic cards you slide into slots in the doors.

There was a computer in every doorknob.
		-- Danny Hillis');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4595,'fortunes',179,'I went to my mother and told her I intended to commence a different life.
I asked for and obtained her blessing and at once commenced the career
of a robber.
		-- Tiburcio Vasquez');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4596,'fortunes',167,'I went to the hardware store and bought some used paint.  It was in
the shape of a house.  I also bought some batteries, but they weren''t
included.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4597,'fortunes',129,'I went to the museum where they had all the heads and arms from the
statues that are in all the other museums.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4598,'fortunes',104,'I went to the race track once and bet on a horse that was so good that
it took seven others to beat him!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4599,'fortunes',48,'I will always love the false image I had of you.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4600,'fortunes',112,'I will follow the good side right to the fire,
but not into it if I can help it.
		-- Michel Eyquem de Montaigne');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4601,'fortunes',308,'I will honour Christmas in my heart, and try to keep it all the
year.  I will live in the Past, the Present, and the Future.  The
Spirits of all Three shall strive within me.  I will not shut out
the lessons that they teach.  Oh, tell me that I may sponge away the
writing on this stone!
		-- Charles Dickens');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4602,'fortunes',53,'I will make you shorter by the head.
		-- Elizabeth I');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4603,'fortunes',24,'I will never lie to you.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4604,'fortunes',59,'I will not be briefed or debriefed, my underwear is my own.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4605,'fortunes',207,'I will not drink!
But if I do...
I will not get drunk!
But if I do...
I will not in public!
But if I do...
I will not fall down!
But if I do...
I will fall face down so that they cannot see my company badge.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4606,'fortunes',22,'I will not forget you.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4607,'fortunes',267,'I will not play at tug o'' war.
I''d rather play at hug o'' war,
Where everyone hugs
Instead of tugs,
Where everyone giggles
And rolls on the rug,
Where everyone kisses,
And everyone grins,
And everyone cuddles,
And everyone wins.
		-- Shel Silverstein, "Hug O'' War"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4608,'fortunes',94,'I will not say that women have no character; rather, they have a new
one every day.
		-- Heine');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4609,'fortunes',147,'I wish a robot would get elected president.  That way, when he came to town,
we could all take a shot at him and not feel too bad.
		-- Jack Handey');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4610,'fortunes',135,'I WISH I HAD A KRYPTONITE CROSS, because then you could keep both Dracula
and Superman away.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4611,'fortunes',157,'I wish there was a knob on the TV where you could turn up the
intelligence.  They''ve got one called brightness, but it doesn''t
seem to work.
		-- Gallagher');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4612,'fortunes',39,'I wish you humans would leave me alone.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4613,'fortunes',38,'I wish you were a Scotch on the rocks.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4614,'fortunes',161,'I woke up a feelin'' mean
went down to play the slot machine
the wheels turned round,
and the letters read
"Better head back to Tennessee Jed"
		-- Grateful Dead');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4615,'fortunes',292,'I woke up this morning and discovered that everything in my apartment
had been stolen and replaced with an exact replica.  I told my roommate,
"Isn''t this amazing?  Everything in the apartment has been stolen and
replaced with an exact replica."  He said, "Do I know you?"
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4616,'fortunes',314,'"I wonder", he said to himself, "what''s in a book while it''s closed.  Oh, I
know it''s full of letters printed on paper, but all the same, something must
be happening, because as soon as I open it, there''s a whole story with people
I don''t know yet and all kinds of adventures and battles."
		-- Bastian B. Bux');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4617,'fortunes',92,'I wonder what the leash and collar set does for excitement?
		-- Tramp, "Lady and the Tramp"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4618,'fortunes',145,'I worked in a health food store once.  A guy came in and asked me,
"If I melt dry ice, can I take a bath without getting wet?"
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4619,'fortunes',284,'I would be batting the big feller if they wasn''t ready with the other one,
but a left-hander would be the thing if they wouldn''t have knowed it already
because there is more things involved than could come up on the road, even
after we''ve been home a long while.
		-- Casey Stengel');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4620,'fortunes',101,'I would gladly raise my voice in praise of women,
only they won''t let me raise my voice.
		-- Winkle');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4621,'fortunes',52,'I would have made a good pope.
		-- Richard M. Nixon');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4622,'fortunes',218,'I would have promised those terrorists a trip to Disneyland if it would have
gotten the hostages released.  I thank God they were satisfied with the
missiles and we didn''t have to go to that extreme.
		-- Oliver North');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4623,'fortunes',390,'I would have you imagine, then, that there exists in the mind of man a block
of wax...  and that we remember and know what is imprinted as long as the
image lasts; but when the image is effaced, or cannot be taken, then we
forget or do not know.
		-- Plato, Dialogs, Theateus 191

	[Quoted in "VMS Internals and Data Structures", V4.4, when
	 referring to image activation and termination.]');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4624,'fortunes',188,'I would like the government to do all it can to mitigate, then, in
understanding, in mutuality of interest, in concern for the common good,
our tasks will be solved.
		-- Warren G. Harding');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4625,'fortunes',125,'I would like to electrocute everyone who uses the word "fair" in connection
with income tax policies.
		-- William F. Buckley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4626,'fortunes',88,'I would like to know
What I was fencing in
And what I was fencing out.
		-- Robert Frost');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4627,'fortunes',100,'I would much rather have men ask why
I have no statue, than why I have one.
		-- Marcus Porcius Cato');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4628,'fortunes',206,'I would not like to be a political leader in Russia.  They never know when
they''re being taped.
		-- Richard M. Nixon

I love America.  You always hurt the one you love.
		-- David Frye impersonating Nixon');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4629,'fortunes',135,'I would rather be a serf in a poor man''s house
and be above ground than reign among the dead.
		-- Achilles, "The Odyssey", XI, 489-91');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4630,'fortunes',99,'I would rather say that a desire to drive fast
sports cars is what sets man apart from the animals.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4631,'fortunes',62,'I wouldn''t be so paranoid if you weren''t all out to get me!!');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4632,'fortunes',43,'I wouldn''t marry her with a ten foot pole.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4633,'fortunes',117,'I wouldn''t recommend sex, drugs or insanity
for everyone, but they''ve always worked for me.
		-- Hunter S. Thompson');
