	Machines should work.  People should think.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4642,'fortunes',58,'IBM''s original motto:
	Cogito ergo vendo; vendo ergo sum.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4643,'fortunes',151,'I''d be a poorer man if I''d never seen an eagle fly.
		-- John Denver

[I saw an eagle fly once.  Fortunately, I had my eagle fly swatter handy.  Ed.]');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4644,'fortunes',42,'I''d give my right arm to be ambidextrous.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4645,'fortunes',54,'I''d horsewhip you if I had a horse.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4646,'fortunes',59,'I''d just as soon kiss a Wookiee.
		-- Princess Leia Organa');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4647,'fortunes',200,'I''D LIKE TO BE BURIED INDIAN-STYLE, where they put you up on a high rack,
above the ground.  That way, you could get hit by meteorites and not even
feel it.
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4648,'fortunes',78,'I''d like to meet the guy who invented beer and see what he''s working on now.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4649,'fortunes',123,'I''d like to see the government get out of war altogether and leave the
whole field to private industry.
		-- Joseph Heller');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4650,'fortunes',82,'I''d love to go out with you, but I did my own thing and now I''ve got
to undo it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4651,'fortunes',73,'I''d love to go out with you, but I have to stay home and see if I
snore.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4652,'fortunes',73,'I''d love to go out with you, but I never go out on days that end in
"Y".');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4653,'fortunes',70,'I''d love to go out with you, but I''m taking punk totem pole carving.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4654,'fortunes',78,'I''d love to go out with you, but the last time I went out, I never
came back.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4655,'fortunes',78,'I''d love to go out with you, but the man on television told me to stay
tuned.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4656,'fortunes',89,'I''d love to kiss you, but I just washed my hair.
		-- Bette Davis, "Cabin in the Cotton"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4657,'fortunes',261,'I''d never cry if I did find
	A blue whale in my soup...
Nor would I mind a porcupine
	Inside a chicken coop.
Yes life is fine when things combine,
	Like ham in beef chow mein...
But lord, this time I think I mind,
	They''ve put acid in my rain.
		-- Milo Bloom');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4658,'fortunes',87,'I''d never join any club that would have the likes of me as a member.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4659,'fortunes',145,'I''d probably settle for a vampire if he were romantic enough.
Couldn''t be any worse than some of the relationships I''ve had.
		-- Brenda Starr');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4660,'fortunes',50,'I''d rather be led to hell than managed to heaven.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4661,'fortunes',65,'I''d rather have a bottle in front of me than a frontal lobotomy.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4662,'fortunes',132,'I''d rather have a free bottle in front of me than a prefrontal lobotomy.
		-- Fred Allen

[Also attributed to S. Clay Wilson.  Ed.]');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4663,'fortunes',76,'I''d rather have two girls at 21 each than one girl at 42.
		-- W. C. Fields');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4664,'fortunes',72,'I''d rather just believe that it''s done by little elves running around.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4665,'fortunes',135,'I''d rather laugh with the sinners,
Than cry with the saints,
The sinners are much more fun!
		-- Billy Joel, "Only The Good Die Young"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4666,'fortunes',51,'I''d rather push my Harley than ride a rice burner.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4667,'fortunes',88,'Ideas don''t stay in some minds very long because they don''t like
solitary confinement.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4668,'fortunes',22,'Identify your visitor.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4669,'fortunes',166,'Idiot Box, n.:
	The part of the envelope that tells a person where to place the
	stamp when they can''t quite figure it out for themselves.
		-- Rich Hall, "Sniglets"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4670,'fortunes',173,'Idiot, n.:
	A member of a large and powerful tribe whose influence in human
	affairs has always been dominant and controlling.
		-- Ambrose Bierce, "The Devil''s Dictionary"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4671,'fortunes',32,'IDLENESS:
	Leisure gone to seed.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4672,'fortunes',33,'Idleness is the holiday of fools.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4673,'fortunes',257,'If 10 years from now, when you are doing something quick
and dirty, you suddenly visualize that I am looking over your
shoulders and say to yourself, "Dijkstra would not have liked this",
well that would be enough immortality for me.
		-- Edsger W. Dijkstra');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4674,'fortunes',88,'If A = B and B = C, then A = C, except where void or prohibited by law.
		-- Roy Santoro');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4675,'fortunes',141,'If a 6600 used paper tape instead of core memory, it would use up tape
at about 30 miles/second.
		-- Grishman, Assembly Language Programming');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4676,'fortunes',76,'If a camel flies, no one laughs if it doesn''t get very far.
		-- Paul White');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4677,'fortunes',116,'If a camel is a horse designed by a committee, then a consensus forecast
is a camel''s behind.
		-- Edgar R. Fiedler');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4678,'fortunes',68,'If a can of Alpo costs 38 cents, would it cost $2.50 in Dog Dollars?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4679,'fortunes',143,'If a child annoys you, quiet him by brushing their hair.  If this doesn''t
work, use the other side of the brush on the other end of the child.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4680,'fortunes',142,'If A equals success, then the formula is _A = _X + _Y + _Z.  _X is work.  _Y
is play.  _Z is keep your mouth shut.
		-- Albert Einstein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4681,'fortunes',72,'If A fool persists in his folly he shall become wise.
		-- William Blake');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4682,'fortunes',140,'If a group of N persons implements a COBOL compiler,
there will be N-1 passes.  Someone in the group has to be the manager.
		-- T. Cheatham');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4683,'fortunes',122,'If a guru falls in the forest with no one to hear him, was he
really a guru at all?
		-- Strange de Jim, "The Metasexuals"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4684,'fortunes',175,'If a jury in a criminal trial stays out for more than twenty-four hours, it
is certain to vote acquittal, save in those instances where it votes guilty.
		-- Joseph C. Goulden');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4685,'fortunes',248,'IF A KID ASKS YOU where rain comes from, I think a cute thing to tell him
is, "God is crying."  And if he asks why God is crying, another cute thing
to tell him is, "Probably because of something you did."
		-- Jack Handey, "The New Mexican" (1988)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4686,'fortunes',78,'If a listener nods his head when you''re
explaining your program, wake him up.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4687,'fortunes',96,'If a man has a strong faith he can indulge in the luxury of skepticism.
		-- Friedrich Nietzsche');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4688,'fortunes',71,'If a man has talent and cannot use it, he has failed.
		-- Thomas Wolfe');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4689,'fortunes',101,'If a man is not a liberal at 25, he has no heart.
If he''s not a conservative by 45, he has no brain.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4690,'fortunes',117,'If a man loses his reverence for any part of life,
he will lose his reverence for all of life.
		-- Albert Schweitzer');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4691,'fortunes',218,'If a man stay away from his wife for seven years, the law presumes the
separation to have killed him; yet according to our daily experience,
it might well prolong his life.
		-- Charles Darling, "Scintillae Juris, 1877');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4692,'fortunes',115,'If a nation expects to be ignorant and free,
... it expects what never was and never will be.
		-- Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4693,'fortunes',191,'If a nation values anything more than freedom, it will lose its freedom;
and the irony of it is that if it is comfort or money it values more, it
will lose that, too.
		-- W. Somerset Maugham');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4694,'fortunes',283,'If a person (a) is poorly, (b) receives treatment intended to make him better,
and (c) gets better, then no power of reasoning known to medical science can
convince him that it may not have been the treatment that restored his health.
		-- Sir Peter Medawar, "The Art of the Soluble"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4695,'fortunes',71,'If a President doesn''t do it to his wife, he''ll do it to his country.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4696,'fortunes',282,'If a putt passes over the hole without dropping, it is deemed to have dropped.
The law of gravity holds that any object attempting to maintain a position
in the atmosphere without something to support it must drop.  The law of
gravity supersedes the law of golf.
		-- Donald A. Metz');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4697,'fortunes',156,'If a shameless woman expects to be defiled and then dies of her fierce
love because you do not consent, will chastity also be homicide?
		-- Saint Augustine');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4698,'fortunes',219,'If a small child asks you where rain comes from, I think a reasonable response
is simply that "God is crying."  And, if he asks you why God is crying, the
only possible answer is "Probably because of something you did."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4699,'fortunes',707,'If a system is administered wisely,
its users will be content.
They enjoy hacking their code
and don''t waste time implementing
labor-saving shell scripts.
Since they dearly love their accounts,
they aren''t interested in other machines.
There may be telnet, rlogin, and ftp,
but these don''t access any hosts.
There may be an arsenal of cracks and malware,
but nobody ever uses them.
People enjoy reading their mail,
take pleasure in being with their newsgroups,
spend weekends working at their terminals,
delight in the doings at the site.
And even though the next system is so close
that users can hear its key clicks and biff beeps,
they are content to die of old age
without ever having gone to see it.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4700,'fortunes',352,'If a team is in a positive frame of mind, it will have a good attitude.
If it has a good attitude, it will make a commitment to playing the
game right.  If it plays the game right, it will win -- unless, of
course, it doesn''t have enough talent to win, and no manager can make
goose-liver pate out of goose feathers, so why worry?
		-- Sparky Anderson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4701,'fortunes',73,'If a thing''s worth doing, it is worth doing badly.
		-- G. K. Chesterton');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4702,'fortunes',71,'If a thing''s worth having, it''s worth cheating for.
		-- W. C. Fields');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4703,'fortunes',73,'If a train station is a place where a train stops, what''s a workstation?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4704,'fortunes',214,'If addiction is judged by how long a dumb animal will sit pressing a lever
to get a "fix" of something, to its own detriment, then I would conclude
that netnews is far more addictive than cocaine.
		-- Rob Stampfli');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4705,'fortunes',171,'If all be true that I do think,
There be five reasons why one should drink;
Good friends, good wine, or being dry,
Or lest we should be by-and-by,
Or any other reason why.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4706,'fortunes',102,'If all else fails, immortality can always be assured by spectacular error.
		-- John Kenneth Galbraith');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4707,'fortunes',40,'If all else fails, lower your standards.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4708,'fortunes',62,'If all men were brothers, would you let one marry your sister?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4709,'fortunes',205,'If all the Chinese simultaneously jumped into the Pacific off a 10 foot
platform erected 10 feet off their coast, it would cause a tidal wave
that would destroy everything in this country west of Nebraska.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4710,'fortunes',192,'If all the seas were ink,
And all the reeds were pens,
And all the skies were parchment,
And all the men could write,
These would not suffice
To write down all the red tape
Of this Government.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4711,'fortunes',78,'If all the world''s a stage, I want to operate the trap door.
		-- Paul Beatty');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4712,'fortunes',105,'If all the world''s economists were laid end to end,
we wouldn''t reach a conclusion.
		-- William Baumol');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4713,'fortunes',607,'If an average person on the subway turns to you, like an ancient mariner,
and starts telling you her tale, you turn away or nod and hope she stops,
not just because you fear she might be crazy.  If she tells her tale on
camera, you might listen.  Watching strangers on television, even
responding to them from a studio audience, we''re disengaged - voyeurs
collaborating with exhibitionists in rituals of sham community.  Never
have so many known so much about people for whom they cared so little.
		-- Wendy Kaminer commenting on testimonial television
		   in "I''m Dysfunctional, You''re Dysfunctional".');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4714,'fortunes',320,'If an S and an I and an O and a U
With an X at the end spell Su;
And an E and a Y and an E spell I,
Pray what is a speller to do?
Then, if also an S and an I and a G
And an HED spell side,
There''s nothing much left for a speller to do
But to go commit siouxeyesighed.
		-- Charles Follen Adams, "An Orthographic Lament"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4715,'fortunes',128,'If any demonstrator ever lays down in front of my car, it''ll be the last
car he ever lays down in front of.
		-- George Wallace');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(4716,'fortunes',103,'If any man wishes to be humbled and mortified,
