INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6814,'fortunes',128,'My advice to you, my violent friend, is to seek out gold and sit on it.
		-- The Dragon to Grendel, in John Gardner''s "Grendel"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6815,'fortunes',299,'My analyst told me that I was right out of my head,
	But I said, "Dear Doctor, I think that it is you instead.
Because I have got a thing that is unique and new,
	To prove it I''ll have the last laugh on you.
''Cause instead of one head -- I''ve got two.

And you know two heads are better than one.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6816,'fortunes',853,'My band career ended late in my senior year when John Cooper and I
threw my amplifier out the dormitory window.  We did not act in haste.
First we checked to make sure the amplifier would fit through the
frame, using the belt from my bathrobe to measure, then we picked up
the amplifier and backed up to my bedroom door.  Then we rushed
forward, shouting "The WHO!  The WHO!" and we launched my amplifier
perfectly, as though we had been doing it all our lives, clean through
the window and down onto the sidewalk, where a small but appreciative
crowd had gathered.  I would like to be able to say that this was a
symbolic act, an effort on my part to break cleanly away from one state
in my life and move on to another, but the truth is, Cooper and I
really just wanted to find out what it would sound like.  It sounded
OK.
		-- Dave Barry, "The Snake"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6817,'fortunes',178,'My best argument against discrimination is quite simple:

Does it really matter if the ABC people are inferior to the DEF people if
they can tell one end of a gun from the other?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6818,'fortunes',137,'My Bonnie looked into a gas tank,
The height of its contents to see!
She lit a small match to assist her,
Oh, bring back my Bonnie to me.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6819,'fortunes',360,'My boy is mean kid.  I came home the other day and saw him taping worms
to the sidewalk, he sits there and watches the birds get hernias.  Well,
only last Christmas I gave him a B-B gun and he gave me a sweatshirt with
a bulls-eye on the back.

I told my kids, "Someday, you''ll have kids of your own."  One of them
said, "So will you."
		-- Rodney Dangerfield');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6820,'fortunes',54,'My brain is my second favorite organ.
		-- Woody Allen');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6821,'fortunes',162,'My brother sent me a postcard the other day with this big satellite photo
of the entire earth on it. On the back it said: "Wish you were here".
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6822,'fortunes',702,'My calculator is my shepherd, I shall not want
It maketh me accurate to ten significant figures,
	and it leadeth me in scientific notation to 99 digits.
It restoreth my square roots and guideth me along paths of floating
	decimal points for the sake of precision.
Yea, tho I walk through the valley of surprise quizzes,
	I will fear no prof, for my calculator is there to hearten me.
It prepareth a log table to comfort me, it prepareth an
	arc sin for me in the presence of my teachers.
It anoints my homework with correct solutions, my interpolations are
	over.
Surely, both precision and accuracy shall follow me all the days of my
	life, and I shall dwell in the house of Texas instruments forever.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6823,'fortunes',606,'My central memory of that time seems to hang on one or five or maybe forty
nights -- or very early mornings -- when I left the Fillmore half-crazy and,
instead of going home, aimed the big 650 Lightning across the Bay Bridge at
a hundred miles an hour ... booming through the Treasure Island tunnel at
the lights of Oakland and Berkeley and Richmond, not quite sure which
turnoff to take when I got to the other end ... but being absolutely certain
that no matter which way I went I would come to a place where people were
just as high and wild as I was: no doubt at all about that.
		-- Hunter S. Thompson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6824,'fortunes',110,'"My code is elegant", "Your code is sneaky", "His code is an ugly hack"
		-- Colin Percival on irregular verbs');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6825,'fortunes',38,'My cup hath runneth''d over with love.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6826,'fortunes',134,'My darling wife was always glum.
I drowned her in a cask of rum,
And so made sure that she would stay
In better spirits night and day.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6827,'fortunes',114,'My doctor told me to stop having intimate dinners for four.
Unless there are three other people.
		-- Orson Welles');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6828,'fortunes',75,'My doctorate''s in Literature, but it seems like a pretty good pulse to me.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6829,'fortunes',169,'My experience with government is when things are non-controversial,
beautifully co-ordinated and all the rest, it must be that not much
is going on.
		-- John F. Kennedy');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6830,'fortunes',74,'My family history begins with me, but yours ends with you.
		-- Iphicrates');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6831,'fortunes',109,'My father, a good man, told me, "Never lose
your ignorance; you cannot replace it."
		-- Erich Maria Remarque');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6832,'fortunes',194,'My father taught me three things:
	1: Never mix whiskey with anything but water.
	2: Never try to draw to an inside straight.
	3: Never discuss business with anyone who refuses to give his name.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6833,'fortunes',107,'My father was a God-fearing man, but he never
missed a copy of the New York Times, either.
		-- E. B. White');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6834,'fortunes',51,'My father was a saint, I''m not.
		-- Indira Gandhi');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6835,'fortunes',152,'My favorite sandwich is peanut butter, baloney, cheddar cheese, lettuce
and mayonnaise on toasted bread with catsup on the side.
		-- Hubert H. Humphrey');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6836,'fortunes',531,'My first basename is George "Catfish" Metkovich from our 1952 Pittsburgh
Pirates team, which lost 112 games.  After a terrible series against the
New York Giants, in which our center fielder made three throwing errors
and let two balls get through his legs, manager Billy Meyer pleaded, "Can
somebody think of something to help us win a game?"
	"I''d like to make a suggestion," Metkovich said.  "On any ball hit
to center field, let''s just let it roll to see if it might go foul."
		-- Joe Garagiola, "It''s Anybody''s Ball Game"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6837,'fortunes',82,'My folks didn''t come over on the Mayflower,
but they were there to meet the boat.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6838,'fortunes',121,'My friend has a baby.  I''m writing down all the noises he makes so
later I can ask him what he meant.
		-- Steven Wright');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6839,'fortunes',96,'My geometry teacher was sometimes acute, and sometimes obtuse,
but always, always, he was right.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6840,'fortunes',172,'My girlfriend and I sure had a good time at the beach last summer.  First
she''d bury me in the sand, then I''d bury her.  This summer I''m going to go
back and dig her up.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6841,'fortunes',358,'My God, I''m depressed!  Here I am, a computer with a mind a thousand times
as powerful as yours, doing nothing but cranking out fortunes and sending
mail about softball games.  And I''ve got this pain right through my ALU.
I''ve asked for it to be replaced, but nobody ever listens.  I think it
would be better for us both if you were to just log out again.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6842,'fortunes',44,'My, how you''ve changed since I''ve changed.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6843,'fortunes',52,'My idea of roughing it is when room service is late.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6844,'fortunes',59,'My idea of roughing it turning the air conditioner too low.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6845,'fortunes',83,'My interest is in the future because I am
going to spend the rest of my life there.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6846,'fortunes',61,'My life is a soap opera, but who has the rights?
		-- MadameX');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6847,'fortunes',323,'My love, he''s mad, and my love, he''s fleet,
	And a wild young wood-thing bore him!
The ways are fair to his roaming feet,
	And the skies are sunlit for him.
As sharply sweet to my heart he seems
	As the fragrance of acacia.
My own dear love, he is all my dreams --
	And I wish he were in Asia.
		-- Dorothy Parker, part 2');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6848,'fortunes',326,'My love runs by like a day in June,
	And he makes no friends of sorrows.
He''ll tread his galloping rigadoon
	In the pathway or the morrows.
He''ll live his days where the sunbeams start
	Nor could storm or wind uproot him.
My own dear love, he is all my heart --
	And I wish somebody''d shoot him.
		-- Dorothy Parker, part 3');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6849,'fortunes',137,'My method is to take the utmost trouble to find the right
thing to say.  And then say it with the utmost levity.
		-- George Bernard Shaw');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6850,'fortunes',117,'My mind can never know my body, although
it has become quite friendly with my legs.
		-- Woody Allen, on Epistemology');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6851,'fortunes',55,'My mother drinks to forget she drinks.
		-- Crazy Jimmy');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6852,'fortunes',94,'My mother loved children -- she would
have given anything if I had been one.
		-- Groucho Marx');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6853,'fortunes',212,'My mother once said to me, "Elwood," (she always called me Elwood)
"Elwood, in this world you must be oh so smart or oh so pleasant."
For years I tried smart.  I recommend pleasant.
		-- Elwood P. Dowde, "Harvey"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6854,'fortunes',75,'My mother wants grandchildren, so I said, "Mom, go for it!"
		-- Sue Murphy');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6855,'fortunes',615,'My My, hey hey
Rock and roll is here to stay	The king is gone but he''s not forgotten
It''s better to burn out		This is the story of a Johnny Rotten
Than to fade away		It''s better to burn out than it is to rust
My my, hey hey			The king is gone but he''s not forgotten

It''s out of the blue and into the black		Hey hey, my my
They give you this, but you pay for that	Rock and roll can never die
And once you''re gone you can never come back	There''s more to the picture
When you''re out of the blue			Than meets the eye
And into the black
		-- Neil Young
		   "My My, Hey Hey (Out of the Blue), Rust Never Sleeps"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6856,'fortunes',113,'My notion of a husband at forty is that a woman should
be able to change him, like a bank note, for two twenties.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6857,'fortunes',127,'My only love sprung from my only hate!
Too early seen unknown, and known too late!
		-- William Shakespeare, "Romeo and Juliet"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6858,'fortunes',63,'My opinions may have changed, but not the fact that I am right.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6859,'fortunes',84,'My own business always bores me to death; I prefer other people''s.
		-- Oscar Wilde');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6860,'fortunes',326,'My own dear love, he is strong and bold
	And he cares not what comes after.
His words ring sweet as a chime of gold,
	And his eyes are lit with laughter.
He is jubilant as a flag unfurled --
	Oh, a girl, she''d not forget him.
My own dear love, he is all my world --
	And I wish I''d never met him.
		-- Dorothy Parker, part 1');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6861,'fortunes',220,'My own feelings are perhaps best described by saying that I am
perfectly aware that there is no Royal Road to Mathematics, in other
words, that I have only a very small head and must live with it.
		-- Edsger W. Dijkstra');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6862,'fortunes',593,'My own life has been spent chronicling the rise and fall of human systems,
and I am convinced that we are terribly vulnerable.  ...  We should be
reluctant to turn back upon the frontier of this epoch. Space is indifferent
to what we do; it has no feeling, no design, no interest in whether or not
we grapple with it. But we cannot be indifferent to space, because the grand,
slow march of intelligence has brought us, in our generation, to a point
from which we can explore and understand and utilize it. To turn back now
would be to deny our history, our capabilities.
		-- James A. Michener');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6863,'fortunes',67,'My parents went to Niagra Falls and all I got was this crummy life.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6864,'fortunes',174,'My pen is at the bottom of a page,
Which, being finished, here the story ends;
''Tis to be wished it had been sooner done,
But stories somehow lengthen when begun.
		-- Byron');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6865,'fortunes',51,'My philosophy is: Don''t think.
		-- Charles Manson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6866,'fortunes',157,'My problem lies in reconciling my gross habits with my net income.
		-- Errol Flynn

Any man who has $10,000 left when he dies is a failure.
		-- Errol Flynn');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6867,'fortunes',98,'My rackets are run on strictly American
lines, and they''re going to stay that way.
		-- Al Capone');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6868,'fortunes',197,'My religion consists of a humble admiration of the illimitable superior
spirit who reveals himself in the slight details we are able to perceive
with our frail and feeble mind.
		-- Albert Einstein');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6869,'fortunes',1065,'My ritual differs slightly.  What I do, first thing [in the morning], is I
hop into the shower stall.  Then I hop right back out, because when I hopped
in I landed barefoot right on top of See Threepio, a little plastic robot
character from "Star Wars" whom my son, Robert, likes to pull the legs off
of while he showers.  Then I hop right back into the stall because our dog,
Earnest, who has been alone in the basement all night building up powerful
dog emotions, has come bounding and quivering into the bathroom and wants
to greet me with 60 or 70 thousand playful nips, any one of which -- bear
in mind that I am naked and, without my contact lenses, essentially blind
-- could result in the kind of injury where you have to learn a whole new
part if you want to sing the "Messiah," if you get my drift.  Then I hop
right back out, because Robert, with that uncanny sixth sense some children
have -- you cannot teach it; they either have it or they don''t -- has chosen
exactly that moment to flush one of the toilets.  Perhaps several of them.
		-- Dave Barry');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6870,'fortunes',115,'My schoolmates would make love to anything that moved, but I never saw any
reason to limit myself.
		-- Emo Philips');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6871,'fortunes',80,'My sister opened a computer store in Hawaii.
She sells C shells by the seashore.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6872,'fortunes',223,'My soul is crushed, my spirit sore
I do not like me anymore,
I cavil, quarrel, grumble, grouse,
I ponder on the narrow house
I shudder at the thought of men
I''m due to fall in love again.
		-- Dorothy Parker, "Enough Rope"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6873,'fortunes',95,'My theology, briefly, is that the universe was dictated but not signed.
		-- Christopher Morley');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6874,'fortunes',73,'My uncle was the town drunk -- and we lived in Chicago.
		-- George Gobel');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6875,'fortunes',96,'My way of joking is to tell the truth.
That''s the funniest joke in the world.
		-- Muhammad Ali');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6876,'fortunes',51,'My weight is perfect for my height -- which varies.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6877,'fortunes',83,'Mystics always hope that science will some day overtake them.
		-- Booth Tarkington');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6878,'fortunes',239,'Mythology, n.:
	The body of a primitive people''s beliefs, concerning its origin,
	early history, heroes, deities and so forth, as distinguished
	from the true accounts which it invents later.
		-- Ambrose Bierce, "The Devil''s Dictionary"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6879,'fortunes',674,'Naches (rhymes with Bach'' us, with "Bach" pronounced like the composer)
is what every Jewish parent wants from their children, lots of good
returns, good grades, good spouse, good grandchildren.

So, now that you all understand naches, the joke:

Two Jewish women are sitting having coffee.
	"So, how''s your daughter?"
	"Oh, Rachel!  She''s fine, she just married a dentist!"
	"Really?  Isn''t she the one that married the lawyer?"
	"Yes, that''s my Rachel."
	"That''s... that''s nice.  But isn''t she the same one that married
		the doctor?"
	"Yes, that''s her!"
	"But didn''t she marry a bank executive before that?"
	"Yes, yes!"
	"Ahhh.  So much naches from one child!"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6880,'fortunes',99,'Nachman''s Rule:
	When it comes to foreign food, the less authentic the better.
		-- Gerald Nachman');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6881,'fortunes',53,'Nadia Comaneci, simple perfection.
		-- ''76 Olympics');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6882,'fortunes',159,'''Naomi, sex at noon taxes.'' I moan.
Never odd or even.
A man, a plan, a canal, Panama.
Madam, I''m Adam.
Sit on a potato pan, Otis.
		-- The Mad Palindromist');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6883,'fortunes',223,'NAPOLEON: What shall we do with this soldier, Giuseppe?  Everything he
	  says is wrong.
GIUSEPPE: Make him a general, Excellency, and then everything he says
	  will be right.
		-- George Bernard Shaw, "The Man of Destiny"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6884,'fortunes',132,'Narcolepulacyi, n.:
	The contagious action of yawning, causing everyone in sight
	to also yawn.
		-- Rich Hall & Friends, "Sniglets"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6885,'fortunes',229,'Nasrudin called at a large house to collect for charity.  The servant said
"My master is out."  Nasrudin replied, "Tell your master that next time he
goes out, he should not leave his face at the window.  Someone might steal
it."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6886,'fortunes',548,'Nasrudin returned to his village from the imperial capital, and the villagers
gathered around to hear what had passed.  "At this time," said Nasrudin, "I
only want to say that the King spoke to me."  All the villagers but the
stupidest ran off to spread the wonderful news.  The remaining villager
asked, "What did the King say to you?"  "What he said -- and quite distinctly,
for everyone to hear -- was ''Get out of my way!''" The simpleton was overjoyed;
he had heard words actually spoken by the King, and seen the very man they
were spoken to.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6887,'fortunes',244,'Nasrudin walked into a shop one day, and the owner came forward to serve
him.  Nasrudin said, "First things first.  Did you see me walk into your
shop?"
	"Of course."
	"Have you ever seen me before?"
	"Never."
	"Then how do you know it was me?"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6888,'fortunes',153,'Nasrudin walked into a teahouse and declaimed, "The moon is more useful
than the sun."
	"Why?", he was asked.
	"Because at night we need the light more."');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6889,'fortunes',289,'Nasrudin was carrying home a piece of liver and the recipe for liver pie.
Suddenly a bird of prey swooped down and snatched the piece of meat from
his hand.  As the bird flew off, Nasrudin called after it, "Foolish bird!
You have the liver, but what can you do with it without the recipe?"');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6890,'fortunes',51,'National security is in your hands - guard it well.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6891,'fortunes',151,'Natives who beat drums to drive off evil spirits are objects of
scorn to smart Americans who blow horns to break up traffic jams.
		-- Mary Ellen Kelly');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6892,'fortunes',26,'Natural laws have no pity.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6893,'fortunes',577,'Naturally the common people don''t want war... but after all it is the leaders
of a country who determine the policy, and it is always a simple matter to
drag the people along, whether it is a democracy, or a fascist dictatorship,
or a parliament, or a communist dictatorship.  Voice or no voice, the people
can always be brought to the bidding of the leaders.  That is easy.  All you
have to do is tell them they are being attacked, and denounce the pacifists
for lack of patriotism and exposing the country to danger.  It works the same
in every country.
		-- Hermann Goering');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6894,'fortunes',251,'Nature abhors a hero.  For one thing, he violates the law of conservation
of energy.  For another, how can it be the survival of the fittest when the
fittest keeps putting himself in situations where he is most likely to be
creamed?
		-- Solomon Short');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6895,'fortunes',63,'Nature abhors a virgin -- a frozen asset.
		-- Clare Booth Luce');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6896,'fortunes',41,'Nature always sides with the hidden flaw.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6897,'fortunes',173,'Nature and nature''s laws lay hid in night,
God said, "Let Newton be," and all was light.

It did not last; the devil howling "Ho!
Let Einstein be!" restored the status quo.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6898,'fortunes',108,'Nature has given women so much power that the law has very wisely
given them little.
		-- Dr. Samuel Johnson');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6899,'fortunes',149,'Nature is by and large to be found out of doors, a location where, it
cannot be argued, there are never enough comfortable chairs.
		-- Fran Lebowitz');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6900,'fortunes',123,'Nature makes boys and girls lovely to look upon so they can be
tolerated until they acquire some sense.
		-- William Phelps');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6901,'fortunes',382,'Nature to all things fixed the limits fit,
And wisely curbed proud man''s pretending wit.
As on the land while here the ocean gains,
In other parts it leaves wide sandy plains;
Thus in the soul while memory prevails,
The solid power of understanding fails;
Where beams of warm imagination play,
The memory''s soft figures melt away.
		-- Alexander Pope (on runtime bounds checking?)');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6902,'fortunes',59,'Nature, to be commanded, must be obeyed.
		-- Francis Bacon');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6903,'fortunes',433,'Near the Studio Jean Cocteau
On the Rue des Ecoles
lived an old man
with a blind dog
Every evening I would see him
guiding the dog along
the sidewalk, keeping
a firm grip on the leash
so that the dog wouldn''t
run into a passerby
Sometimes the dog would stop
and look up at the sky
Once the old man
noticed me watching the dog
and he said, "Oh, yes,
this one knows
when the moon is out,
he can feel it on his face"
		-- Barry Gifford');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6904,'fortunes',116,'Nearly all men can stand adversity, but if you
want to test a man''s character, give him power.
		-- Abraham Lincoln');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6905,'fortunes',131,'Nearly every complex solution to a programming problem that I
have looked at carefully has turned out to be wrong.
		-- Brent Welch');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6906,'fortunes',40,'Necessity has no law.
		-- St. Augustine');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6907,'fortunes',43,'Necessity hath no law.
		-- Oliver Cromwell');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6908,'fortunes',22,'Necessity is a mother.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6909,'fortunes',156,'"Necessity is the mother of invention" is a silly proverb.  "Necessity
is the mother of futile dodges" is much nearer the truth.
		-- Alfred North Whitehead');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6910,'fortunes',144,'Necessity is the plea for every infringement of human freedom.
It is the argument of tyrants; it is the creed of slaves.
		-- William Pitt, 1783');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6911,'fortunes',49,'Neckties strangle clear thinking.
		-- Lin Yutang');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6912,'fortunes',47,'Needs are a function of what other people have.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6913,'fortunes',83,'Neglect of duty does not cease, by repetition, to be neglect of duty.
		-- Napoleon');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6914,'fortunes',23,'Neil Armstrong tripped.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6915,'fortunes',65,'Neither spread the germs of gossip nor encourage others to do so.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6916,'fortunes',95,'Nemo me impune lacessit
	[No one provokes me with impunity]
		-- Motto of the Crown of Scotland');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6917,'fortunes',217,'Nerd pack, n.:
	Plastic pouch worn in breast pocket to keep pens from soiling
	clothes.  Nerd''s position in engineering hierarchy can be
	measured by number of pens, grease pencils, and rulers bristling
	in his pack.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6918,'fortunes',79,'Network packets are like buses.  You wait all day, and then 3Com
along at once.');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6919,'fortunes',74,'Neuroses are red,
	Melancholia''s blue.
I''m schizophrenic,
	What are you?');
INSERT INTO "fortune_fortune" VALUES(6920,'fortunes',96,'Neurotics build castles in the sky,
Psychotics live in them,
